4099 ExprResult E = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, Kind, VK_RValue, &BasePath, CCK);
4100 if (E.isInvalid())
4101 return ExprError();
4102 else
4103 From = E.get();
4104
4105 break;
4106 }
4107
4108 case ICK_Pointer_Member: {
4109 CastKind Kind;
4110 CXXCastPath BasePath;
4111 if (CheckMemberPointerConversion(From, ToType, Kind, BasePath, CStyle))
4112 return ExprError();
4113 if (CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(From, ToType))
4114 return ExprError();
4115
4116 // We may not have been able to figure out what this member pointer resolved
4117 // to up until this exact point. Attempt to lock-in it's inheritance model.
4118 if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
4119 (void)isCompleteType(From->getExprLoc(), From->getType());
4120 (void)isCompleteType(From->getExprLoc(), ToType);
4121 }
4122
4123 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, Kind, VK_RValue, &BasePath, CCK)
4124 .get();
4125 break;
4126 }
4127
4128 case ICK_Boolean_Conversion:
4129 // Perform half-to-boolean conversion via float.
4130 if (From->getType()->isHalfType()) {
4131 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, Context.FloatTy, CK_FloatingCast).get();
4132 FromType = Context.FloatTy;
4133 }
4134
4135 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, Context.BoolTy,
4136 ScalarTypeToBooleanCastKind(FromType),
4137 VK_RValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4138 break;
4139
4140 case ICK_Derived_To_Base: {
4141 CXXCastPath BasePath;
4142 if (CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(
4143 From->getType(), ToType.getNonReferenceType(), From->getBeginLoc(),
4144 From->getSourceRange(), &BasePath, CStyle))
4145 return ExprError();
4146
4147 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType.getNonReferenceType(),
4148 CK_DerivedToBase, From->getValueKind(),
4149 &BasePath, CCK).get();
4150 break;
4151 }
4152
4153 case ICK_Vector_Conversion:
4154 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_BitCast,
4155 VK_RValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4156 break;
4157
4158 case ICK_Vector_Splat: {
4159 // Vector splat from any arithmetic type to a vector.
4160 Expr *Elem = prepareVectorSplat(ToType, From).get();
4161 From = ImpCastExprToType(Elem, ToType, CK_VectorSplat, VK_RValue,
4162 /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4163 break;
4164 }
4165
4166 case ICK_Complex_Real:
4167 // Case 1. x -> _Complex y
4168 if (const ComplexType *ToComplex = ToType->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4169 QualType ElType = ToComplex->getElementType();
4170 bool isFloatingComplex = ElType->isRealFloatingType();
4171
4172 // x -> y
4173 if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ElType, From->getType())) {
4174 // do nothing
4175 } else if (From->getType()->isRealFloatingType()) {
4176 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ElType,
4177 isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingCast : CK_FloatingToIntegral).get();
4178 } else {
4179 assert(From->getType()->isIntegerType());
4180 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ElType,
4181 isFloatingComplex ? CK_IntegralToFloating : CK_IntegralCast).get();
4182 }
4183 // y -> _Complex y
4184 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4185 isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingRealToComplex
4186 : CK_IntegralRealToComplex).get();
4187
4188 // Case 2. _Complex x -> y
4189 } else {
4190 const ComplexType *FromComplex = From->getType()->getAs<ComplexType>();
4191 assert(FromComplex);
4192
4193 QualType ElType = FromComplex->getElementType();
4194 bool isFloatingComplex = ElType->isRealFloatingType();
4195
4196 // _Complex x -> x
4197 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ElType,
4198 isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingComplexToReal
4199 : CK_IntegralComplexToReal,
4200 VK_RValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4201
4202 // x -> y
4203 if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ElType, ToType)) {
4204 // do nothing
4205 } else if (ToType->isRealFloatingType()) {
4206 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4207 isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingCast : CK_IntegralToFloating,
4208 VK_RValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4209 } else {
4210 assert(ToType->isIntegerType());
4211 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4212 isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingToIntegral : CK_IntegralCast,
4213 VK_RValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4214 }
4215 }
4216 break;
4217
4218 case ICK_Block_Pointer_Conversion: {
4219 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType.getUnqualifiedType(), CK_BitCast,
4220 VK_RValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4221 break;
4222 }
4223
4224 case ICK_TransparentUnionConversion: {
4225 ExprResult FromRes = From;
4226 Sema::AssignConvertType ConvTy =
4227 CheckTransparentUnionArgumentConstraints(ToType, FromRes);
4228 if (FromRes.isInvalid())
4229 return ExprError();
4230 From = FromRes.get();
4231 assert ((ConvTy == Sema::Compatible) &&
4232 "Improper transparent union conversion");
4233 (void)ConvTy;
4234 break;
4235 }
4236
4237 case ICK_Zero_Event_Conversion:
4238 case ICK_Zero_Queue_Conversion:
4239 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4240 CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType,
4241 From->getValueKind()).get();
4242 break;
4243
4244 case ICK_Lvalue_To_Rvalue:
4245 case ICK_Array_To_Pointer:
4246 case ICK_Function_To_Pointer:
4247 case ICK_Function_Conversion:
4248 case ICK_Qualification:
4249 case ICK_Num_Conversion_Kinds:
4250 case ICK_C_Only_Conversion:
4251 case ICK_Incompatible_Pointer_Conversion:
4252 llvm_unreachable("Improper second standard conversion");
4253 }
4254
4255 switch (SCS.Third) {
4256 case ICK_Identity:
4257 // Nothing to do.
4258 break;
4259
4260 case ICK_Function_Conversion:
4261 // If both sides are functions (or pointers/references to them), there could
4262 // be incompatible exception declarations.
4263 if (CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(From, ToType))
4264 return ExprError();
4265
4266 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_NoOp,
4267 VK_RValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4268 break;
4269
4270 case ICK_Qualification: {
4271 // The qualification keeps the category of the inner expression, unless the
4272 // target type isn't a reference.
4273 ExprValueKind VK =
4274 ToType->isReferenceType() ? From->getValueKind() : VK_RValue;
4275
4276 CastKind CK = CK_NoOp;
4277
4278 if (ToType->isReferenceType() &&
4279 ToType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() !=
4280 From->getType().getAddressSpace())
4281 CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
4282
4283 if (ToType->isPointerType() &&
4284 ToType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() !=
4285 From->getType()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace())
4286 CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
4287
4288 const bool FromIsCap = FromType->isCHERICapabilityType(Context);
4289 const bool ToIsCap = ToType->isCHERICapabilityType(Context);
4290 if (FromIsCap != ToIsCap) {
4291 if (SCS.isInvalidCHERICapabilityConversion()) {
4292 unsigned DiagID = FromIsCap ? diag::err_typecheck_convert_cap_to_ptr :
4293 diag::err_typecheck_convert_ptr_to_cap;
4294 Diag(From->getBeginLoc(), DiagID) << FromType << ToType << false
4295 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(From->getBeginLoc(), "(__cheri_" +
4296 std::string(FromIsCap ? "from" : "to") +
4297 "cap " + ToType.getAsString() + ")");
4298 return ExprError();
4299 }
4300 CK = FromIsCap ? CK_CHERICapabilityToPointer : CK_PointerToCHERICapability;
4301 }
4302 // ImpCastExprToType may return an ExprError, so cache the current value of
4303 Expr *FromOld = From;
4304 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType.getNonLValueExprType(Context), CK, VK,
4305 /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4306 .get();
4307
4308 if (SCS.DeprecatedStringLiteralToCharPtr &&
4309 !getLangOpts().WritableStrings) {
4310 Diag(FromOld->getBeginLoc(),
4311 getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11
4312 ? diag::ext_deprecated_string_literal_conversion
4313 : diag::warn_deprecated_string_literal_conversion)
4314 << ToType.getNonReferenceType();
4315 }
4316
4317 if (!From)
4318 return ExprError();
4319
4320 break;
4321 }
4322
4323 default:
4324 llvm_unreachable("Improper third standard conversion");
4325 }
4326
4327 // If this conversion sequence involved a scalar -> atomic conversion, perform
4328 // that conversion now.
4329 if (!ToAtomicType.isNull()) {
4330 assert(Context.hasSameType(
4331 ToAtomicType->castAs<AtomicType>()->getValueType(), From->getType()));
4332 From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToAtomicType, CK_NonAtomicToAtomic,
4333 VK_RValue, nullptr, CCK).get();
4334 }
4335
4336 // If this conversion sequence succeeded and involved implicitly converting a
4337 // _Nullable type to a _Nonnull one, complain.
4338 if (!isCast(CCK))
4339 diagnoseNullableToNonnullConversion(ToType, InitialFromType,
4340 From->getBeginLoc());
4341
4342 return From;
4343}
4344
4345/// Check the completeness of a type in a unary type trait.
4346///
4347/// If the particular type trait requires a complete type, tries to complete
4348/// it. If completing the type fails, a diagnostic is emitted and false
4349/// returned. If completing the type succeeds or no completion was required,
4350/// returns true.
4351static bool CheckUnaryTypeTraitTypeCompleteness(Sema &S, TypeTrait UTT,
4352 SourceLocation Loc,
4353 QualType ArgTy) {
4354 // C++0x [meta.unary.prop]p3:
4355 // For all of the class templates X declared in this Clause, instantiating
4356 // that template with a template argument that is a class template
4357 // specialization may result in the implicit instantiation of the template
4358 // argument if and only if the semantics of X require that the argument
4359 // must be a complete type.
4360 // We apply this rule to all the type trait expressions used to implement
4361 // these class templates. We also try to follow any GCC documented behavior
4362 // in these expressions to ensure portability of standard libraries.
4363 switch (UTT) {
4364 default: llvm_unreachable("not a UTT");
4365 // is_complete_type somewhat obviously cannot require a complete type.
4366 case UTT_IsCompleteType:
4367 // Fall-through
4368
4369 // These traits are modeled on the type predicates in C++0x
4370 // [meta.unary.cat] and [meta.unary.comp]. They are not specified as
4371 // requiring a complete type, as whether or not they return true cannot be
4372 // impacted by the completeness of the type.
4373 case UTT_IsVoid:
4374 case UTT_IsIntegral:
4375 case UTT_IsFloatingPoint:
4376 case UTT_IsArray:
4377 case UTT_IsPointer:
4378 case UTT_IsLvalueReference:
4379 case UTT_IsRvalueReference:
4380 case UTT_IsMemberFunctionPointer:
4381 case UTT_IsMemberObjectPointer:
4382 case UTT_IsEnum:
4383 case UTT_IsUnion:
4384 case UTT_IsClass:
4385 case UTT_IsFunction:
4386 case UTT_IsReference:
4387 case UTT_IsArithmetic:
4388 case UTT_IsFundamental:
4389 case UTT_IsObject:
4390 case UTT_IsScalar:
4391 case UTT_IsCompound:
4392 case UTT_IsMemberPointer:
4393 // Fall-through
4394
4395 // These traits are modeled on type predicates in C++0x [meta.unary.prop]
4396 // which requires some of its traits to have the complete type. However,
4397 // the completeness of the type cannot impact these traits' semantics, and
4398 // so they don't require it. This matches the comments on these traits in
4399 // Table 49.
4400 case UTT_IsConst:
4401 case UTT_IsVolatile:
4402 case UTT_IsSigned:
4403 case UTT_IsUnsigned:
4404
4405 // This type trait always returns false, checking the type is moot.
4406 case UTT_IsInterfaceClass:
4407 return true;
4408
4409 // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
4410 // If T is a non-union class type, T shall be a complete type.
4411 case UTT_IsEmpty:
4412 case UTT_IsPolymorphic:
4413 case UTT_IsAbstract:
4414 if (const auto *RD = ArgTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4415 if (!RD->isUnion())
4416 return !S.RequireCompleteType(
4417 Loc, ArgTy, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr);
4418 return true;
4419
4420 // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
4421 // If T is a class type, T shall be a complete type.
4422 case UTT_IsFinal:
4423 case UTT_IsSealed:
4424 if (ArgTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4425 return !S.RequireCompleteType(
4426 Loc, ArgTy, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr);
4427 return true;
4428
4429 // C++1z [meta.unary.prop]:
4430 // remove_all_extents_t<T> shall be a complete type or cv void.
4431 case UTT_IsAggregate:
4432 case UTT_IsTrivial:
4433 case UTT_IsTriviallyCopyable:
4434 case UTT_IsStandardLayout:
4435 case UTT_IsPOD:
4436 case UTT_IsLiteral:
4437 // Per the GCC type traits documentation, T shall be a complete type, cv void,
4438 // or an array of unknown bound. But GCC actually imposes the same constraints
4439 // as above.
4440 case UTT_HasNothrowAssign:
4441 case UTT_HasNothrowMoveAssign:
4442 case UTT_HasNothrowConstructor:
4443 case UTT_HasNothrowCopy:
4444 case UTT_HasTrivialAssign:
4445 case UTT_HasTrivialMoveAssign:
4446 case UTT_HasTrivialDefaultConstructor:
4447 case UTT_HasTrivialMoveConstructor:
4448 case UTT_HasTrivialCopy:
4449 case UTT_HasTrivialDestructor:
4450 case UTT_HasVirtualDestructor:
4451 ArgTy = QualType(ArgTy->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe(), 0);
4452 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4453
4454 // C++1z [meta.unary.prop]:
4455 // T shall be a complete type, cv void, or an array of unknown bound.
4456 case UTT_IsDestructible:
4457 case UTT_IsNothrowDestructible:
4458 case UTT_IsTriviallyDestructible:
4459 case UTT_HasUniqueObjectRepresentations:
4460 if (ArgTy->isIncompleteArrayType() || ArgTy->isVoidType())
4461 return true;
4462
4463 return !S.RequireCompleteType(
4464 Loc, ArgTy, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr);
4465 }
4466}
4467
4468static bool HasNoThrowOperator(const RecordType *RT, OverloadedOperatorKind Op,
4469 Sema &Self, SourceLocation KeyLoc, ASTContext &C,
4470 bool (CXXRecordDecl::*HasTrivial)() const,
4471 bool (CXXRecordDecl::*HasNonTrivial)() const,
4472 bool (CXXMethodDecl::*IsDesiredOp)() const)
4473{
4474 CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
4475 if ((RD->*HasTrivial)() && !(RD->*HasNonTrivial)())
4476 return true;
4477
4478 DeclarationName Name = C.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op);
4479 DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo(Name, KeyLoc);
4480 LookupResult Res(Self, NameInfo, Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
4481 if (Self.LookupQualifiedName(Res, RD)) {
4482 bool FoundOperator = false;
4483 Res.suppressDiagnostics();
4484 for (LookupResult::iterator Op = Res.begin(), OpEnd = Res.end();
4485 Op != OpEnd; ++Op) {
4486 if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(*Op))
4487 continue;
4488
4489 CXXMethodDecl *Operator = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(*Op);
4490 if((Operator->*IsDesiredOp)()) {
4491 FoundOperator = true;
4492 const FunctionProtoType *CPT =
4493 Operator->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
4494 CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
4495 if (!CPT || !CPT->isNothrow())
4496 return false;
4497 }
4498 }
4499 return FoundOperator;
4500 }
4501 return false;
4502}
4503
4504static bool EvaluateUnaryTypeTrait(Sema &Self, TypeTrait UTT,
4505 SourceLocation KeyLoc, QualType T) {
4506 assert(!T->isDependentType() && "Cannot evaluate traits of dependent type");
4507
4508 ASTContext &C = Self.Context;
4509 switch(UTT) {
4510 default: llvm_unreachable("not a UTT");
4511 // Type trait expressions corresponding to the primary type category
4512 // predicates in C++0x [meta.unary.cat].
4513 case UTT_IsVoid:
4514 return T->isVoidType();
4515 case UTT_IsIntegral:
4516 return T->isIntegralType(C);
4517 case UTT_IsFloatingPoint:
4518 return T->isFloatingType();
4519 case UTT_IsArray:
4520 return T->isArrayType();
4521 case UTT_IsPointer:
4522 return T->isPointerType();
4523 case UTT_IsLvalueReference:
4524 return T->isLValueReferenceType();
4525 case UTT_IsRvalueReference:
4526 return T->isRValueReferenceType();
4527 case UTT_IsMemberFunctionPointer:
4528 return T->isMemberFunctionPointerType();
4529 case UTT_IsMemberObjectPointer:
4530 return T->isMemberDataPointerType();
4531 case UTT_IsEnum:
4532 return T->isEnumeralType();
4533 case UTT_IsUnion:
4534 return T->isUnionType();
4535 case UTT_IsClass:
4536 return T->isClassType() || T->isStructureType() || T->isInterfaceType();
4537 case UTT_IsFunction:
4538 return T->isFunctionType();
4539
4540 // Type trait expressions which correspond to the convenient composition
4541 // predicates in C++0x [meta.unary.comp].
4542 case UTT_IsReference:
4543 return T->isReferenceType();
4544 case UTT_IsArithmetic:
4545 return T->isArithmeticType() && !T->isEnumeralType();
4546 case UTT_IsFundamental:
4547 return T->isFundamentalType();
4548 case UTT_IsObject:
4549 return T->isObjectType();
4550 case UTT_IsScalar:
4551 // Note: semantic analysis depends on Objective-C lifetime types to be
4552 // considered scalar types. However, such types do not actually behave
4553 // like scalar types at run time (since they may require retain/release
4554 // operations), so we report them as non-scalar.
4555 if (T->isObjCLifetimeType()) {
4556 switch (T.getObjCLifetime()) {
4557 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4558 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4559 return true;
4560
4561 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4562 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4563 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4564 return false;
4565 }
4566 }
4567
4568 return T->isScalarType();
4569 case UTT_IsCompound:
4570 return T->isCompoundType();
4571 case UTT_IsMemberPointer:
4572 return T->isMemberPointerType();
4573
4574 // Type trait expressions which correspond to the type property predicates
4575 // in C++0x [meta.unary.prop].
4576 case UTT_IsConst:
4577 return T.isConstQualified();
4578 case UTT_IsVolatile:
4579 return T.isVolatileQualified();
4580 case UTT_IsTrivial:
4581 return T.isTrivialType(C);
4582 case UTT_IsTriviallyCopyable:
4583 return T.isTriviallyCopyableType(C);
4584 case UTT_IsStandardLayout:
4585 return T->isStandardLayoutType();
4586 case UTT_IsPOD:
4587 return T.isPODType(C);
4588 case UTT_IsLiteral:
4589 return T->isLiteralType(C);
4590 case UTT_IsEmpty:
4591 if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4592 return !RD->isUnion() && RD->isEmpty();
4593 return false;
4594 case UTT_IsPolymorphic:
4595 if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4596 return !RD->isUnion() && RD->isPolymorphic();
4597 return false;
4598 case UTT_IsAbstract:
4599 if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4600 return !RD->isUnion() && RD->isAbstract();
4601 return false;
4602 case UTT_IsAggregate:
4603 // Report vector extensions and complex types as aggregates because they
4604 // support aggregate initialization. GCC mirrors this behavior for vectors
4605 // but not _Complex.
4606 return T->isAggregateType() || T->isVectorType() || T->isExtVectorType() ||
4607 T->isAnyComplexType();
4608 // __is_interface_class only returns true when CL is invoked in /CLR mode and
4609 // even then only when it is used with the 'interface struct ...' syntax
4610 // Clang doesn't support /CLR which makes this type trait moot.
4611 case UTT_IsInterfaceClass:
4612 return false;
4613 case UTT_IsFinal:
4614 case UTT_IsSealed:
4615 if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4616 return RD->hasAttr<FinalAttr>();
4617 return false;
4618 case UTT_IsSigned:
4619 return T->isSignedIntegerType();
4620 case UTT_IsUnsigned:
4621 return T->isUnsignedIntegerType();
4622
4623 // Type trait expressions which query classes regarding their construction,
4624 // destruction, and copying. Rather than being based directly on the
4625 // related type predicates in the standard, they are specified by both
4626 // GCC[1] and the Embarcadero C++ compiler[2], and Clang implements those
4627 // specifications.
4628 //
4629 // 1: http://gcc.gnu/.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html
4630 // 2: http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE/en/Type_Trait_Functions_(C%2B%2B0x)_Index
4631 //
4632 // Note that these builtins do not behave as documented in g++: if a class
4633 // has both a trivial and a non-trivial special member of a particular kind,
4634 // they return false! For now, we emulate this behavior.
4635 // FIXME: This appears to be a g++ bug: more complex cases reveal that it
4636 // does not correctly compute triviality in the presence of multiple special
4637 // members of the same kind. Revisit this once the g++ bug is fixed.
4638 case UTT_HasTrivialDefaultConstructor:
4639 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
4640 // If __is_pod (type) is true then the trait is true, else if type is
4641 // a cv class or union type (or array thereof) with a trivial default
4642 // constructor ([class.ctor]) then the trait is true, else it is false.
4643 if (T.isPODType(C))
4644 return true;
4645 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4646 return RD->hasTrivialDefaultConstructor() &&
4647 !RD->hasNonTrivialDefaultConstructor();
4648 return false;
4649 case UTT_HasTrivialMoveConstructor:
4650 // This trait is implemented by MSVC 2012 and needed to parse the
4651 // standard library headers. Specifically this is used as the logic
4652 // behind std::is_trivially_move_constructible (20.9.4.3).
4653 if (T.isPODType(C))
4654 return true;
4655 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4656 return RD->hasTrivialMoveConstructor() && !RD->hasNonTrivialMoveConstructor();
4657 return false;
4658 case UTT_HasTrivialCopy:
4659 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
4660 // If __is_pod (type) is true or type is a reference type then
4661 // the trait is true, else if type is a cv class or union type
4662 // with a trivial copy constructor ([class.copy]) then the trait
4663 // is true, else it is false.
4664 if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isReferenceType())
4665 return true;
4666 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4667 return RD->hasTrivialCopyConstructor() &&
4668 !RD->hasNonTrivialCopyConstructor();
4669 return false;
4670 case UTT_HasTrivialMoveAssign:
4671 // This trait is implemented by MSVC 2012 and needed to parse the
4672 // standard library headers. Specifically it is used as the logic
4673 // behind std::is_trivially_move_assignable (20.9.4.3)
4674 if (T.isPODType(C))
4675 return true;
4676 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4677 return RD->hasTrivialMoveAssignment() && !RD->hasNonTrivialMoveAssignment();
4678 return false;
4679 case UTT_HasTrivialAssign:
4680 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
4681 // If type is const qualified or is a reference type then the
4682 // trait is false. Otherwise if __is_pod (type) is true then the
4683 // trait is true, else if type is a cv class or union type with
4684 // a trivial copy assignment ([class.copy]) then the trait is
4685 // true, else it is false.
4686 // Note: the const and reference restrictions are interesting,
4687 // given that const and reference members don't prevent a class
4688 // from having a trivial copy assignment operator (but do cause
4689 // errors if the copy assignment operator is actually used, q.v.
4690 // [class.copy]p12).
4691
4692 if (T.isConstQualified())
4693 return false;
4694 if (T.isPODType(C))
4695 return true;
4696 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4697 return RD->hasTrivialCopyAssignment() &&
4698 !RD->hasNonTrivialCopyAssignment();
4699 return false;
4700 case UTT_IsDestructible:
4701 case UTT_IsTriviallyDestructible:
4702 case UTT_IsNothrowDestructible:
4703 // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
4704 // For reference types, is_destructible<T>::value is true.
4705 if (T->isReferenceType())
4706 return true;
4707
4708 // Objective-C++ ARC: autorelease types don't require destruction.
4709 if (T->isObjCLifetimeType() &&
4710 T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing)
4711 return true;
4712
4713 // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
4714 // For incomplete types and function types, is_destructible<T>::value is
4715 // false.
4716 if (T->isIncompleteType() || T->isFunctionType())
4717 return false;
4718
4719 // A type that requires destruction (via a non-trivial destructor or ARC
4720 // lifetime semantics) is not trivially-destructible.
4721 if (UTT == UTT_IsTriviallyDestructible && T.isDestructedType())
4722 return false;
4723
4724 // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
4725 // For object types and given U equal to remove_all_extents_t<T>, if the
4726 // expression std::declval<U&>().~U() is well-formed when treated as an
4727 // unevaluated operand (Clause 5), then is_destructible<T>::value is true
4728 if (auto *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
4729 CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = Self.LookupDestructor(RD);
4730 if (!Destructor)
4731 return false;
4732 // C++14 [dcl.fct.def.delete]p2:
4733 // A program that refers to a deleted function implicitly or
4734 // explicitly, other than to declare it, is ill-formed.
4735 if (Destructor->isDeleted())
4736 return false;
4737 if (C.getLangOpts().AccessControl && Destructor->getAccess() != AS_public)
4738 return false;
4739 if (UTT == UTT_IsNothrowDestructible) {
4740 const FunctionProtoType *CPT =
4741 Destructor->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
4742 CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
4743 if (!CPT || !CPT->isNothrow())
4744 return false;
4745 }
4746 }
4747 return true;
4748
4749 case UTT_HasTrivialDestructor:
4750 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html
4751 // If __is_pod (type) is true or type is a reference type
4752 // then the trait is true, else if type is a cv class or union
4753 // type (or array thereof) with a trivial destructor
4754 // ([class.dtor]) then the trait is true, else it is
4755 // false.
4756 if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isReferenceType())
4757 return true;
4758
4759 // Objective-C++ ARC: autorelease types don't require destruction.
4760 if (T->isObjCLifetimeType() &&
4761 T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing)
4762 return true;
4763
4764 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4765 return RD->hasTrivialDestructor();
4766 return false;
4767 // TODO: Propagate nothrowness for implicitly declared special members.
4768 case UTT_HasNothrowAssign:
4769 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
4770 // If type is const qualified or is a reference type then the
4771 // trait is false. Otherwise if __has_trivial_assign (type)
4772 // is true then the trait is true, else if type is a cv class
4773 // or union type with copy assignment operators that are known
4774 // not to throw an exception then the trait is true, else it is
4775 // false.
4776 if (C.getBaseElementType(T).isConstQualified())
4777 return false;
4778 if (T->isReferenceType())
4779 return false;
4780 if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isObjCLifetimeType())
4781 return true;
4782
4783 if (const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>())
4784 return HasNoThrowOperator(RT, OO_Equal, Self, KeyLoc, C,
4785 &CXXRecordDecl::hasTrivialCopyAssignment,
4786 &CXXRecordDecl::hasNonTrivialCopyAssignment,
4787 &CXXMethodDecl::isCopyAssignmentOperator);
4788 return false;
4789 case UTT_HasNothrowMoveAssign:
4790 // This trait is implemented by MSVC 2012 and needed to parse the
4791 // standard library headers. Specifically this is used as the logic
4792 // behind std::is_nothrow_move_assignable (20.9.4.3).
4793 if (T.isPODType(C))
4794 return true;
4795
4796 if (const RecordType *RT = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAs<RecordType>())
4797 return HasNoThrowOperator(RT, OO_Equal, Self, KeyLoc, C,
4798 &CXXRecordDecl::hasTrivialMoveAssignment,
4799 &CXXRecordDecl::hasNonTrivialMoveAssignment,
4800 &CXXMethodDecl::isMoveAssignmentOperator);
4801 return false;
4802 case UTT_HasNothrowCopy:
4803 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
4804 // If __has_trivial_copy (type) is true then the trait is true, else
4805 // if type is a cv class or union type with copy constructors that are
4806 // known not to throw an exception then the trait is true, else it is
4807 // false.
4808 if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isReferenceType() || T->isObjCLifetimeType())
4809 return true;
4810 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
4811 if (RD->hasTrivialCopyConstructor() &&
4812 !RD->hasNonTrivialCopyConstructor())
4813 return true;
4814
4815 bool FoundConstructor = false;
4816 unsigned FoundTQs;
4817 for (const auto *ND : Self.LookupConstructors(RD)) {
4818 // A template constructor is never a copy constructor.
4819 // FIXME: However, it may actually be selected at the actual overload
4820 // resolution point.
4821 if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl()))
4822 continue;
4823 // UsingDecl itself is not a constructor
4824 if (isa<UsingDecl>(ND))
4825 continue;
4826 auto *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl());
4827 if (Constructor->isCopyConstructor(FoundTQs)) {
4828 FoundConstructor = true;
4829 const FunctionProtoType *CPT
4830 = Constructor->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
4831 CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
4832 if (!CPT)
4833 return false;
4834 // TODO: check whether evaluating default arguments can throw.
4835 // For now, we'll be conservative and assume that they can throw.
4836 if (!CPT->isNothrow() || CPT->getNumParams() > 1)
4837 return false;
4838 }
4839 }
4840
4841 return FoundConstructor;
4842 }
4843 return false;
4844 case UTT_HasNothrowConstructor:
4845 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html
4846 // If __has_trivial_constructor (type) is true then the trait is
4847 // true, else if type is a cv class or union type (or array
4848 // thereof) with a default constructor that is known not to
4849 // throw an exception then the trait is true, else it is false.
4850 if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isObjCLifetimeType())
4851 return true;
4852 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
4853 if (RD->hasTrivialDefaultConstructor() &&
4854 !RD->hasNonTrivialDefaultConstructor())
4855 return true;
4856
4857 bool FoundConstructor = false;
4858 for (const auto *ND : Self.LookupConstructors(RD)) {
4859 // FIXME: In C++0x, a constructor template can be a default constructor.
4860 if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl()))
4861 continue;
4862 // UsingDecl itself is not a constructor
4863 if (isa<UsingDecl>(ND))
4864 continue;
4865 auto *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl());
4866 if (Constructor->isDefaultConstructor()) {
4867 FoundConstructor = true;
4868 const FunctionProtoType *CPT
4869 = Constructor->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
4870 CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
4871 if (!CPT)
4872 return false;
4873 // FIXME: check whether evaluating default arguments can throw.
4874 // For now, we'll be conservative and assume that they can throw.
4875 if (!CPT->isNothrow() || CPT->getNumParams() > 0)
4876 return false;
4877 }
4878 }
4879 return FoundConstructor;
4880 }
4881 return false;
4882 case UTT_HasVirtualDestructor:
4883 // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
4884 // If type is a class type with a virtual destructor ([class.dtor])
4885 // then the trait is true, else it is false.
4886 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4887 if (CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = Self.LookupDestructor(RD))
4888 return Destructor->isVirtual();
4889 return false;
4890
4891 // These type trait expressions are modeled on the specifications for the
4892 // Embarcadero C++0x type trait functions:
4893 // http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE/en/Type_Trait_Functions_(C%2B%2B0x)_Index
4894 case UTT_IsCompleteType:
4895 // http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE/en/Is_complete_type_(typename_T_):
4896 // Returns True if and only if T is a complete type at the point of the
4897 // function call.
4898 return !T->isIncompleteType();
4899 case UTT_HasUniqueObjectRepresentations:
4900 return C.hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(T);
4901 }
4902}
4903
4904static bool EvaluateBinaryTypeTrait(Sema &Self, TypeTrait BTT, QualType LhsT,
4905 QualType RhsT, SourceLocation KeyLoc);
4906
4907static bool evaluateTypeTrait(Sema &S, TypeTrait Kind, SourceLocation KWLoc,
4908 ArrayRef<TypeSourceInfo *> Args,
4909 SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
4910 if (Kind <= UTT_Last)
4911 return EvaluateUnaryTypeTrait(S, Kind, KWLoc, Args[0]->getType());
4912
4913 // Evaluate BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary alongside the IsConstructible
4914 // traits to avoid duplication.
4915 if (Kind <= BTT_Last && Kind != BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary)
4916 return EvaluateBinaryTypeTrait(S, Kind, Args[0]->getType(),
4917 Args[1]->getType(), RParenLoc);
4918
4919 switch (Kind) {
4920 case clang::BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary:
4921 case clang::TT_IsConstructible:
4922 case clang::TT_IsNothrowConstructible:
4923 case clang::TT_IsTriviallyConstructible: {
4924 // C++11 [meta.unary.prop]:
4925 // is_trivially_constructible is defined as:
4926 //
4927 // is_constructible<T, Args...>::value is true and the variable
4928 // definition for is_constructible, as defined below, is known to call
4929 // no operation that is not trivial.
4930 //
4931 // The predicate condition for a template specialization
4932 // is_constructible<T, Args...> shall be satisfied if and only if the
4933 // following variable definition would be well-formed for some invented
4934 // variable t:
4935 //
4936 // T t(create<Args>()...);
4937 assert(!Args.empty());
4938
4939 // Precondition: T and all types in the parameter pack Args shall be
4940 // complete types, (possibly cv-qualified) void, or arrays of
4941 // unknown bound.
4942 for (const auto *TSI : Args) {
4943 QualType ArgTy = TSI->getType();
4944 if (ArgTy->isVoidType() || ArgTy->isIncompleteArrayType())
4945 continue;
4946
4947 if (S.RequireCompleteType(KWLoc, ArgTy,
4948 diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
4949 return false;
4950 }
4951
4952 // Make sure the first argument is not incomplete nor a function type.
4953 QualType T = Args[0]->getType();
4954 if (T->isIncompleteType() || T->isFunctionType())
4955 return false;
4956
4957 // Make sure the first argument is not an abstract type.
4958 CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4959 if (RD && RD->isAbstract())
4960 return false;
4961
4962 SmallVector<OpaqueValueExpr, 2> OpaqueArgExprs;
4963 SmallVector<Expr *, 2> ArgExprs;
4964 ArgExprs.reserve(Args.size() - 1);
4965 for (unsigned I = 1, N = Args.size(); I != N; ++I) {
4966 QualType ArgTy = Args[I]->getType();
4967 if (ArgTy->isObjectType() || ArgTy->isFunctionType())
4968 ArgTy = S.Context.getRValueReferenceType(ArgTy);
4969 OpaqueArgExprs.push_back(
4970 OpaqueValueExpr(Args[I]->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
4971 ArgTy.getNonLValueExprType(S.Context),
4972 Expr::getValueKindForType(ArgTy)));
4973 }
4974 for (Expr &E : OpaqueArgExprs)
4975 ArgExprs.push_back(&E);
4976
4977 // Perform the initialization in an unevaluated context within a SFINAE
4978 // trap at translation unit scope.
4979 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
4980 S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
4981 Sema::SFINAETrap SFINAE(S, /*AccessCheckingSFINAE=*/true);
4982 Sema::ContextRAII TUContext(S, S.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
4983 InitializedEntity To(InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(Args[0]));
4984 InitializationKind InitKind(InitializationKind::CreateDirect(KWLoc, KWLoc,
4985 RParenLoc));
4986 InitializationSequence Init(S, To, InitKind, ArgExprs);
4987 if (Init.Failed())
4988 return false;
4989
4990 ExprResult Result = Init.Perform(S, To, InitKind, ArgExprs);
4991 if (Result.isInvalid() || SFINAE.hasErrorOccurred())
4992 return false;
4993
4994 if (Kind == clang::TT_IsConstructible)
4995 return true;
4996
4997 if (Kind == clang::BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary) {
4998 if (!T->isReferenceType())
4999 return false;
5000
5001 return !Init.isDirectReferenceBinding();
5002 }
5003
5004 if (Kind == clang::TT_IsNothrowConstructible)
5005 return S.canThrow(Result.get()) == CT_Cannot;
5006
5007 if (Kind == clang::TT_IsTriviallyConstructible) {
5008 // Under Objective-C ARC and Weak, if the destination has non-trivial
5009 // Objective-C lifetime, this is a non-trivial construction.
5010 if (T.getNonReferenceType().hasNonTrivialObjCLifetime())
5011 return false;
5012
5013 // The initialization succeeded; now make sure there are no non-trivial
5014 // calls.
5015 return !Result.get()->hasNonTrivialCall(S.Context);
5016 }
5017
5018 llvm_unreachable("unhandled type trait");
5019 return false;
5020 }
5021 default: llvm_unreachable("not a TT");
5022 }
5023
5024 return false;
5025}
5026
5027ExprResult Sema::BuildTypeTrait(TypeTrait Kind, SourceLocation KWLoc,
5028 ArrayRef<TypeSourceInfo *> Args,
5029 SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
5030 QualType ResultType = Context.getLogicalOperationType();
5031
5032 if (Kind <= UTT_Last && !CheckUnaryTypeTraitTypeCompleteness(
5033 *this, Kind, KWLoc, Args[0]->getType()))
5034 return ExprError();
5035
5036 bool Dependent = false;
5037 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Args.size(); I != N; ++I) {
5038 if (Args[I]->getType()->isDependentType()) {
5039 Dependent = true;
5040 break;
5041 }
5042 }
5043
5044 bool Result = false;
5045 if (!Dependent)
5046 Result = evaluateTypeTrait(*this, Kind, KWLoc, Args, RParenLoc);
5047
5048 return TypeTraitExpr::Create(Context, ResultType, KWLoc, Kind, Args,
5049 RParenLoc, Result);
5050}
5051
5052ExprResult Sema::ActOnTypeTrait(TypeTrait Kind, SourceLocation KWLoc,
5053 ArrayRef<ParsedType> Args,
5054 SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
5055 SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> ConvertedArgs;
5056 ConvertedArgs.reserve(Args.size());
5057
5058 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Args.size(); I != N; ++I) {
5059 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo;
5060 QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(Args[I], &TInfo);
5061 if (!TInfo)
5062 TInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, KWLoc);
5063
5064 ConvertedArgs.push_back(TInfo);
5065 }
5066
5067 return BuildTypeTrait(Kind, KWLoc, ConvertedArgs, RParenLoc);
5068}
5069
5070static bool EvaluateBinaryTypeTrait(Sema &Self, TypeTrait BTT, QualType LhsT,
5071 QualType RhsT, SourceLocation KeyLoc) {
5072 assert(!LhsT->isDependentType() && !RhsT->isDependentType() &&
5073 "Cannot evaluate traits of dependent types");
5074
5075 switch(BTT) {
5076 case BTT_IsBaseOf: {
5077 // C++0x [meta.rel]p2
5078 // Base is a base class of Derived without regard to cv-qualifiers or
5079 // Base and Derived are not unions and name the same class type without
5080 // regard to cv-qualifiers.
5081
5082 const RecordType *lhsRecord = LhsT->getAs<RecordType>();
5083 const RecordType *rhsRecord = RhsT->getAs<RecordType>();
5084 if (!rhsRecord || !lhsRecord) {
5085 const ObjCObjectType *LHSObjTy = LhsT->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
5086 const ObjCObjectType *RHSObjTy = RhsT->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
5087 if (!LHSObjTy || !RHSObjTy)
5088 return false;
5089
5090 ObjCInterfaceDecl *BaseInterface = LHSObjTy->getInterface();
5091 ObjCInterfaceDecl *DerivedInterface = RHSObjTy->getInterface();
5092 if (!BaseInterface || !DerivedInterface)
5093 return false;
5094
5095 if (Self.RequireCompleteType(
5096 KeyLoc, RhsT, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
5097 return false;
5098
5099 return BaseInterface->isSuperClassOf(DerivedInterface);
5100 }
5101
5102 assert(Self.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(LhsT, RhsT)
5103 == (lhsRecord == rhsRecord));
5104
5105 // Unions are never base classes, and never have base classes.
5106 // It doesn't matter if they are complete or not. See PR#41843
5107 if (lhsRecord && lhsRecord->getDecl()->isUnion())
5108 return false;
5109 if (rhsRecord && rhsRecord->getDecl()->isUnion())
5110 return false;
5111
5112 if (lhsRecord == rhsRecord)
5113 return true;
5114
5115 // C++0x [meta.rel]p2:
5116 // If Base and Derived are class types and are different types
5117 // (ignoring possible cv-qualifiers) then Derived shall be a
5118 // complete type.
5119 if (Self.RequireCompleteType(KeyLoc, RhsT,
5120 diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
5121 return false;
5122
5123 return cast<CXXRecordDecl>(rhsRecord->getDecl())
5124 ->isDerivedFrom(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(lhsRecord->getDecl()));
5125 }
5126 case BTT_IsSame:
5127 return Self.Context.hasSameType(LhsT, RhsT);
5128 case BTT_TypeCompatible: {
5129 // GCC ignores cv-qualifiers on arrays for this builtin.
5130 Qualifiers LhsQuals, RhsQuals;
5131 QualType Lhs = Self.getASTContext().getUnqualifiedArrayType(LhsT, LhsQuals);
5132 QualType Rhs = Self.getASTContext().getUnqualifiedArrayType(RhsT, RhsQuals);
5133 return Self.Context.typesAreCompatible(Lhs, Rhs);
5134 }
5135 case BTT_IsConvertible:
5136 case BTT_IsConvertibleTo: {
5137 // C++0x [meta.rel]p4:
5138 // Given the following function prototype:
5139 //
5140 // template <class T>
5141 // typename add_rvalue_reference<T>::type create();
5142 //
5143 // the predicate condition for a template specialization
5144 // is_convertible<From, To> shall be satisfied if and only if
5145 // the return expression in the following code would be
5146 // well-formed, including any implicit conversions to the return
5147 // type of the function:
5148 //
5149 // To test() {
5150 // return create<From>();
5151 // }
5152 //
5153 // Access checking is performed as if in a context unrelated to To and
5154 // From. Only the validity of the immediate context of the expression
5155 // of the return-statement (including conversions to the return type)
5156 // is considered.
5157 //
5158 // We model the initialization as a copy-initialization of a temporary
5159 // of the appropriate type, which for this expression is identical to the
5160 // return statement (since NRVO doesn't apply).
5161
5162 // Functions aren't allowed to return function or array types.
5163 if (RhsT->isFunctionType() || RhsT->isArrayType())
5164 return false;
5165
5166 // A return statement in a void function must have void type.
5167 if (RhsT->isVoidType())
5168 return LhsT->isVoidType();
5169
5170 // A function definition requires a complete, non-abstract return type.
5171 if (!Self.isCompleteType(KeyLoc, RhsT) || Self.isAbstractType(KeyLoc, RhsT))
5172 return false;
5173
5174 // Compute the result of add_rvalue_reference.
5175 if (LhsT->isObjectType() || LhsT->isFunctionType())
5176 LhsT = Self.Context.getRValueReferenceType(LhsT);
5177
5178 // Build a fake source and destination for initialization.
5179 InitializedEntity To(InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(RhsT));
5180 OpaqueValueExpr From(KeyLoc, LhsT.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context),
5181 Expr::getValueKindForType(LhsT));
5182 Expr *FromPtr = &From;
5183 InitializationKind Kind(InitializationKind::CreateCopy(KeyLoc,
5184 SourceLocation()));
5185
5186 // Perform the initialization in an unevaluated context within a SFINAE
5187 // trap at translation unit scope.
5188 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5189 Self, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
5190 Sema::SFINAETrap SFINAE(Self, /*AccessCheckingSFINAE=*/true);
5191 Sema::ContextRAII TUContext(Self, Self.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
5192 InitializationSequence Init(Self, To, Kind, FromPtr);
5193 if (Init.Failed())
5194 return false;
5195
5196 ExprResult Result = Init.Perform(Self, To, Kind, FromPtr);
5197 return !Result.isInvalid() && !SFINAE.hasErrorOccurred();
5198 }
5199
5200 case BTT_IsAssignable:
5201 case BTT_IsNothrowAssignable:
5202 case BTT_IsTriviallyAssignable: {
5203 // C++11 [meta.unary.prop]p3:
5204 // is_trivially_assignable is defined as:
5205 // is_assignable<T, U>::value is true and the assignment, as defined by
5206 // is_assignable, is known to call no operation that is not trivial
5207 //
5208 // is_assignable is defined as:
5209 // The expression declval<T>() = declval<U>() is well-formed when
5210 // treated as an unevaluated operand (Clause 5).
5211 //
5212 // For both, T and U shall be complete types, (possibly cv-qualified)
5213 // void, or arrays of unknown bound.
5214 if (!LhsT->isVoidType() && !LhsT->isIncompleteArrayType() &&
5215 Self.RequireCompleteType(KeyLoc, LhsT,
5216 diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
5217 return false;
5218 if (!RhsT->isVoidType() && !RhsT->isIncompleteArrayType() &&
5219 Self.RequireCompleteType(KeyLoc, RhsT,
5220 diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
5221 return false;
5222
5223 // cv void is never assignable.
5224 if (LhsT->isVoidType() || RhsT->isVoidType())
5225 return false;
5226
5227 // Build expressions that emulate the effect of declval<T>() and
5228 // declval<U>().
5229 if (LhsT->isObjectType() || LhsT->isFunctionType())
5230 LhsT = Self.Context.getRValueReferenceType(LhsT);
5231 if (RhsT->isObjectType() || RhsT->isFunctionType())
5232 RhsT = Self.Context.getRValueReferenceType(RhsT);
5233 OpaqueValueExpr Lhs(KeyLoc, LhsT.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context),
5234 Expr::getValueKindForType(LhsT));
5235 OpaqueValueExpr Rhs(KeyLoc, RhsT.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context),
5236 Expr::getValueKindForType(RhsT));
5237
5238 // Attempt the assignment in an unevaluated context within a SFINAE
5239 // trap at translation unit scope.
5240 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5241 Self, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
5242 Sema::SFINAETrap SFINAE(Self, /*AccessCheckingSFINAE=*/true);
5243 Sema::ContextRAII TUContext(Self, Self.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
5244 ExprResult Result = Self.BuildBinOp(/*S=*/nullptr, KeyLoc, BO_Assign, &Lhs,
5245 &Rhs);
5246 if (Result.isInvalid() || SFINAE.hasErrorOccurred())
5247 return false;
5248
5249 if (BTT == BTT_IsAssignable)
5250 return true;
5251
5252 if (BTT == BTT_IsNothrowAssignable)
5253 return Self.canThrow(Result.get()) == CT_Cannot;
5254
5255 if (BTT == BTT_IsTriviallyAssignable) {
5256 // Under Objective-C ARC and Weak, if the destination has non-trivial
5257 // Objective-C lifetime, this is a non-trivial assignment.
5258 if (LhsT.getNonReferenceType().hasNonTrivialObjCLifetime())
5259 return false;
5260
5261 return !Result.get()->hasNonTrivialCall(Self.Context);
5262 }
5263
5264 llvm_unreachable("unhandled type trait");
5265 return false;
5266 }
5267 default: llvm_unreachable("not a BTT");
5268 }
5269 llvm_unreachable("Unknown type trait or not implemented");
5270}
5271
5272ExprResult Sema::ActOnArrayTypeTrait(ArrayTypeTrait ATT,
5273 SourceLocation KWLoc,
5274 ParsedType Ty,
5275 Expr* DimExpr,
5276 SourceLocation RParen) {
5277 TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo;
5278 QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(Ty, &TSInfo);
5279 if (!TSInfo)
5280 TSInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T);
5281
5282 return BuildArrayTypeTrait(ATT, KWLoc, TSInfo, DimExpr, RParen);
5283}
5284
5285static uint64_t EvaluateArrayTypeTrait(Sema &Self, ArrayTypeTrait ATT,
5286 QualType T, Expr *DimExpr,
5287 SourceLocation KeyLoc) {
5288 assert(!T->isDependentType() && "Cannot evaluate traits of dependent type");
5289
5290 switch(ATT) {
5291 case ATT_ArrayRank:
5292 if (T->isArrayType()) {
5293 unsigned Dim = 0;
5294 while (const ArrayType *AT = Self.Context.getAsArrayType(T)) {
5295 ++Dim;
5296 T = AT->getElementType();
5297 }
5298 return Dim;
5299 }
5300 return 0;
5301
5302 case ATT_ArrayExtent: {
5303 llvm::APSInt Value;
5304 uint64_t Dim;
5305 if (Self.VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(DimExpr, &Value,
5306 diag::err_dimension_expr_not_constant_integer,
5307 false).isInvalid())
5308 return 0;
5309 if (Value.isSigned() && Value.isNegative()) {
5310 Self.Diag(KeyLoc, diag::err_dimension_expr_not_constant_integer)
5311 << DimExpr->getSourceRange();
5312 return 0;
5313 }
5314 Dim = Value.getLimitedValue();
5315
5316 if (T->isArrayType()) {
5317 unsigned D = 0;
5318 bool Matched = false;
5319 while (const ArrayType *AT = Self.Context.getAsArrayType(T)) {
5320 if (Dim == D) {
5321 Matched = true;
5322 break;
5323 }
5324 ++D;
5325 T = AT->getElementType();
5326 }
5327
5328 if (Matched && T->isArrayType()) {
5329 if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = Self.Context.getAsConstantArrayType(T))
5330 return CAT->getSize().getLimitedValue();
5331 }
5332 }
5333 return 0;
5334 }
5335 }
5336 llvm_unreachable("Unknown type trait or not implemented");
5337}
5338
5339ExprResult Sema::BuildArrayTypeTrait(ArrayTypeTrait ATT,
5340 SourceLocation KWLoc,
5341 TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo,
5342 Expr* DimExpr,
5343 SourceLocation RParen) {
5344 QualType T = TSInfo->getType();
5345
5346 // FIXME: This should likely be tracked as an APInt to remove any host
5347 // assumptions about the width of size_t on the target.
5348 uint64_t Value = 0;
5349 if (!T->isDependentType())
5350 Value = EvaluateArrayTypeTrait(*this, ATT, T, DimExpr, KWLoc);
5351
5352 // While the specification for these traits from the Embarcadero C++
5353 // compiler's documentation says the return type is 'unsigned int', Clang
5354 // returns 'size_t'. On Windows, the primary platform for the Embarcadero
5355 // compiler, there is no difference. On several other platforms this is an
5356 // important distinction.
5357 return new (Context) ArrayTypeTraitExpr(KWLoc, ATT, TSInfo, Value, DimExpr,
5358 RParen, Context.getSizeType());
5359}
5360
5361ExprResult Sema::ActOnExpressionTrait(ExpressionTrait ET,
5362 SourceLocation KWLoc,
5363 Expr *Queried,
5364 SourceLocation RParen) {
5365 // If error parsing the expression, ignore.
5366 if (!Queried)
5367 return ExprError();
5368
5369 ExprResult Result = BuildExpressionTrait(ET, KWLoc, Queried, RParen);
5370
5371 return Result;
5372}
5373
5374static bool EvaluateExpressionTrait(ExpressionTrait ET, Expr *E) {
5375 switch (ET) {
5376 case ET_IsLValueExpr: return E->isLValue();
5377 case ET_IsRValueExpr: return E->isRValue();
5378 }
5379 llvm_unreachable("Expression trait not covered by switch");
5380}
5381
5382ExprResult Sema::BuildExpressionTrait(ExpressionTrait ET,
5383 SourceLocation KWLoc,
5384 Expr *Queried,
5385 SourceLocation RParen) {
5386 if (Queried->isTypeDependent()) {
5387 // Delay type-checking for type-dependent expressions.
5388 } else if (Queried->getType()->isPlaceholderType()) {
5389 ExprResult PE = CheckPlaceholderExpr(Queried);
5390 if (PE.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
5391 return BuildExpressionTrait(ET, KWLoc, PE.get(), RParen);
5392 }
5393
5394 bool Value = EvaluateExpressionTrait(ET, Queried);
5395
5396 return new (Context)
5397 ExpressionTraitExpr(KWLoc, ET, Queried, Value, RParen, Context.BoolTy);
5398}
5399
5400QualType Sema::CheckPointerToMemberOperands(ExprResult &LHS, ExprResult &RHS,
5401 ExprValueKind &VK,
5402 SourceLocation Loc,
5403 bool isIndirect) {
5404 assert(!LHS.get()->getType()->isPlaceholderType() &&
5405 !RHS.get()->getType()->isPlaceholderType() &&
5406 "placeholders should have been weeded out by now");
5407
5408 // The LHS undergoes lvalue conversions if this is ->*, and undergoes the
5409 // temporary materialization conversion otherwise.
5410 if (isIndirect)
5411 LHS = DefaultLvalueConversion(LHS.get());
5412 else if (LHS.get()->isRValue())
5413 LHS = TemporaryMaterializationConversion(LHS.get());
5414 if (LHS.isInvalid())
5415 return QualType();
5416
5417 // The RHS always undergoes lvalue conversions.
5418 RHS = DefaultLvalueConversion(RHS.get());
5419 if (RHS.isInvalid()) return QualType();
5420
5421 const char *OpSpelling = isIndirect ? "->*" : ".*";
5422 // C++ 5.5p2
5423 // The binary operator .* [p3: ->*] binds its second operand, which shall
5424 // be of type "pointer to member of T" (where T is a completely-defined
5425 // class type) [...]
5426 QualType RHSType = RHS.get()->getType();
5427 const MemberPointerType *MemPtr = RHSType->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
5428 if (!MemPtr) {
5429 Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_memptr_rhs)
5430 << OpSpelling << RHSType << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5431 return QualType();
5432 }
5433
5434 QualType Class(MemPtr->getClass(), 0);
5435
5436 // Note: C++ [expr.mptr.oper]p2-3 says that the class type into which the
5437 // member pointer points must be completely-defined. However, there is no
5438 // reason for this semantic distinction, and the rule is not enforced by
5439 // other compilers. Therefore, we do not check this property, as it is
5440 // likely to be considered a defect.
5441
5442 // C++ 5.5p2
5443 // [...] to its first operand, which shall be of class T or of a class of
5444 // which T is an unambiguous and accessible base class. [p3: a pointer to
5445 // such a class]
5446 QualType LHSType = LHS.get()->getType();
5447 if (isIndirect) {
5448 if (const PointerType *Ptr = LHSType->getAs<PointerType>())
5449 LHSType = Ptr->getPointeeType();
5450 else {
5451 Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_memptr_lhs)
5452 << OpSpelling << 1 << LHSType
5453 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(SourceRange(Loc), ".*");
5454 return QualType();
5455 }
5456 }
5457
5458 if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(Class, LHSType)) {
5459 // If we want to check the hierarchy, we need a complete type.
5460 if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, LHSType, diag::err_bad_memptr_lhs,
5461 OpSpelling, (int)isIndirect)) {
5462 return QualType();
5463 }
5464
5465 if (!IsDerivedFrom(Loc, LHSType, Class)) {
5466 Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_memptr_lhs) << OpSpelling
5467 << (int)isIndirect << LHS.get()->getType();
5468 return QualType();
5469 }
5470
5471 CXXCastPath BasePath;
5472 if (CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(
5473 LHSType, Class, Loc,
5474 SourceRange(LHS.get()->getBeginLoc(), RHS.get()->getEndLoc()),
5475 &BasePath))
5476 return QualType();
5477
5478 // Cast LHS to type of use.
5479 QualType UseType = Context.getQualifiedType(Class, LHSType.getQualifiers());
5480 if (isIndirect)
5481 UseType = Context.getPointerType(UseType);
5482 ExprValueKind VK = isIndirect ? VK_RValue : LHS.get()->getValueKind();
5483 LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), UseType, CK_DerivedToBase, VK,
5484 &BasePath);
5485 }
5486
5487 if (isa<CXXScalarValueInitExpr>(RHS.get()->IgnoreParens())) {
5488 // Diagnose use of pointer-to-member type which when used as
5489 // the functional cast in a pointer-to-member expression.
5490 Diag(Loc, diag::err_pointer_to_member_type) << isIndirect;
5491 return QualType();
5492 }
5493
5494 // C++ 5.5p2
5495 // The result is an object or a function of the type specified by the
5496 // second operand.
5497 // The cv qualifiers are the union of those in the pointer and the left side,
5498 // in accordance with 5.5p5 and 5.2.5.
5499 QualType Result = MemPtr->getPointeeType();
5500 Result = Context.getCVRQualifiedType(Result, LHSType.getCVRQualifiers());
5501
5502 // C++0x [expr.mptr.oper]p6:
5503 // In a .* expression whose object expression is an rvalue, the program is
5504 // ill-formed if the second operand is a pointer to member function with
5505 // ref-qualifier &. In a ->* expression or in a .* expression whose object
5506 // expression is an lvalue, the program is ill-formed if the second operand
5507 // is a pointer to member function with ref-qualifier &&.
5508 if (const FunctionProtoType *Proto = Result->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
5509 switch (Proto->getRefQualifier()) {
5510 case RQ_None:
5511 // Do nothing
5512 break;
5513
5514 case RQ_LValue:
5515 if (!isIndirect && !LHS.get()->Classify(Context).isLValue()) {
5516 // C++2a allows functions with ref-qualifier & if their cv-qualifier-seq
5517 // is (exactly) 'const'.
5518 if (Proto->isConst() && !Proto->isVolatile())
5519 Diag(Loc, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus2a
5520 ? diag::warn_cxx17_compat_pointer_to_const_ref_member_on_rvalue
5521 : diag::ext_pointer_to_const_ref_member_on_rvalue);
5522 else
5523 Diag(Loc, diag::err_pointer_to_member_oper_value_classify)
5524 << RHSType << 1 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5525 }
5526 break;
5527
5528 case RQ_RValue:
5529 if (isIndirect || !LHS.get()->Classify(Context).isRValue())
5530 Diag(Loc, diag::err_pointer_to_member_oper_value_classify)
5531 << RHSType << 0 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5532 break;
5533 }
5534 }
5535
5536 // C++ [expr.mptr.oper]p6:
5537 // The result of a .* expression whose second operand is a pointer
5538 // to a data member is of the same value category as its
5539 // first operand. The result of a .* expression whose second
5540 // operand is a pointer to a member function is a prvalue. The
5541 // result of an ->* expression is an lvalue if its second operand
5542 // is a pointer to data member and a prvalue otherwise.
5543 if (Result->isFunctionType()) {
5544 VK = VK_RValue;
5545 return Context.BoundMemberTy;
5546 } else if (isIndirect) {
5547 VK = VK_LValue;
5548 } else {
5549 VK = LHS.get()->getValueKind();
5550 }
5551
5552 return Result;
5553}
5554
5555/// Try to convert a type to another according to C++11 5.16p3.
5556///
5557/// This is part of the parameter validation for the ? operator. If either
5558/// value operand is a class type, the two operands are attempted to be
5559/// converted to each other. This function does the conversion in one direction.
5560/// It returns true if the program is ill-formed and has already been diagnosed
5561/// as such.
5562static bool TryClassUnification(Sema &Self, Expr *From, Expr *To,
5563 SourceLocation QuestionLoc,
5564 bool &HaveConversion,
5565 QualType &ToType) {
5566 HaveConversion = false;
5567 ToType = To->getType();
5568
5569 InitializationKind Kind =
5570 InitializationKind::CreateCopy(To->getBeginLoc(), SourceLocation());
5571 // C++11 5.16p3
5572 // The process for determining whether an operand expression E1 of type T1
5573 // can be converted to match an operand expression E2 of type T2 is defined
5574 // as follows:
5575 // -- If E2 is an lvalue: E1 can be converted to match E2 if E1 can be
5576 // implicitly converted to type "lvalue reference to T2", subject to the
5577 // constraint that in the conversion the reference must bind directly to
5578 // an lvalue.
5579 // -- If E2 is an xvalue: E1 can be converted to match E2 if E1 can be
5580 // implicitly converted to the type "rvalue reference to R2", subject to
5581 // the constraint that the reference must bind directly.
5582 if (To->isLValue() || To->isXValue()) {
5583 QualType T = To->isLValue() ? Self.Context.getLValueReferenceType(ToType)
5584 : Self.Context.getRValueReferenceType(ToType);
5585
5586 InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(T);
5587
5588 InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
5589 if (InitSeq.isDirectReferenceBinding()) {
5590 ToType = T;
5591 HaveConversion = true;
5592 return false;
5593 }
5594
5595 if (InitSeq.isAmbiguous())
5596 return InitSeq.Diagnose(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
5597 }
5598
5599 // -- If E2 is an rvalue, or if the conversion above cannot be done:
5600 // -- if E1 and E2 have class type, and the underlying class types are
5601 // the same or one is a base class of the other:
5602 QualType FTy = From->getType();
5603 QualType TTy = To->getType();
5604 const RecordType *FRec = FTy->getAs<RecordType>();
5605 const RecordType *TRec = TTy->getAs<RecordType>();
5606 bool FDerivedFromT = FRec && TRec && FRec != TRec &&
5607 Self.IsDerivedFrom(QuestionLoc, FTy, TTy);
5608 if (FRec && TRec && (FRec == TRec || FDerivedFromT ||
5609 Self.IsDerivedFrom(QuestionLoc, TTy, FTy))) {
5610 // E1 can be converted to match E2 if the class of T2 is the
5611 // same type as, or a base class of, the class of T1, and
5612 // [cv2 > cv1].
5613 if (FRec == TRec || FDerivedFromT) {
5614 if (TTy.isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(FTy)) {
5615 InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(TTy);
5616 InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
5617 if (InitSeq) {
5618 HaveConversion = true;
5619 return false;
5620 }
5621
5622 if (InitSeq.isAmbiguous())
5623 return InitSeq.Diagnose(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
5624 }
5625 }
5626
5627 return false;
5628 }
5629
5630 // -- Otherwise: E1 can be converted to match E2 if E1 can be
5631 // implicitly converted to the type that expression E2 would have
5632 // if E2 were converted to an rvalue (or the type it has, if E2 is
5633 // an rvalue).
5634 //
5635 // This actually refers very narrowly to the lvalue-to-rvalue conversion, not
5636 // to the array-to-pointer or function-to-pointer conversions.
5637 TTy = TTy.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context);
5638
5639 InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(TTy);
5640 InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
5641 HaveConversion = !InitSeq.Failed();
5642 ToType = TTy;
5643 if (InitSeq.isAmbiguous())
5644 return InitSeq.Diagnose(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
5645
5646 return false;
5647}
5648
5649/// Try to find a common type for two according to C++0x 5.16p5.
5650///
5651/// This is part of the parameter validation for the ? operator. If either
5652/// value operand is a class type, overload resolution is used to find a
5653/// conversion to a common type.
5654static bool FindConditionalOverload(Sema &Self, ExprResult &LHS, ExprResult &RHS,
5655 SourceLocation QuestionLoc) {
5656 Expr *Args[2] = { LHS.get(), RHS.get() };
5657 OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(QuestionLoc,
5658 OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator);
5659 Self.AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates(OO_Conditional, QuestionLoc, Args,
5660 CandidateSet);
5661
5662 OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
5663 switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(Self, QuestionLoc, Best)) {
5664 case OR_Success: {
5665 // We found a match. Perform the conversions on the arguments and move on.
5666 ExprResult LHSRes = Self.PerformImplicitConversion(
5667 LHS.get(), Best->BuiltinParamTypes[0], Best->Conversions[0],
5668 Sema::AA_Converting);
5669 if (LHSRes.isInvalid())
5670 break;
5671 LHS = LHSRes;
5672
5673 ExprResult RHSRes = Self.PerformImplicitConversion(
5674 RHS.get(), Best->BuiltinParamTypes[1], Best->Conversions[1],
5675 Sema::AA_Converting);
5676 if (RHSRes.isInvalid())
5677 break;
5678 RHS = RHSRes;
5679 if (Best->Function)
5680 Self.MarkFunctionReferenced(QuestionLoc, Best->Function);
5681 return false;
5682 }
5683
5684 case OR_No_Viable_Function:
5685
5686 // Emit a better diagnostic if one of the expressions is a null pointer
5687 // constant and the other is a pointer type. In this case, the user most
5688 // likely forgot to take the address of the other expression.
5689 if (Self.DiagnoseConditionalForNull(LHS.get(), RHS.get(), QuestionLoc))
5690 return true;
5691
5692 Self.Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_typecheck_cond_incompatible_operands)
5693 << LHS.get()->getType() << RHS.get()->getType()
5694 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5695 return true;
5696
5697 case OR_Ambiguous:
5698 Self.Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_ambiguous_ovl)
5699 << LHS.get()->getType() << RHS.get()->getType()
5700 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5701 // FIXME: Print the possible common types by printing the return types of
5702 // the viable candidates.
5703 break;
5704
5705 case OR_Deleted:
5706 llvm_unreachable("Conditional operator has only built-in overloads");
5707 }
5708 return true;
5709}
5710
5711/// Perform an "extended" implicit conversion as returned by
5712/// TryClassUnification.
5713static bool ConvertForConditional(Sema &Self, ExprResult &E, QualType T) {
5714 InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(T);
5715 InitializationKind Kind =
5716 InitializationKind::CreateCopy(E.get()->getBeginLoc(), SourceLocation());
5717 Expr *Arg = E.get();
5718 InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, Arg);
5719 ExprResult Result = InitSeq.Perform(Self, Entity, Kind, Arg);
5720 if (Result.isInvalid())
5721 return true;
5722
5723 E = Result;
5724 return false;
5725}
5726
5727/// Check the operands of ?: under C++ semantics.
5728///
5729/// See C++ [expr.cond]. Note that LHS is never null, even for the GNU x ?: y
5730/// extension. In this case, LHS == Cond. (But they're not aliases.)
5731QualType Sema::CXXCheckConditionalOperands(ExprResult &Cond, ExprResult &LHS,
5732 ExprResult &RHS, ExprValueKind &VK,
5733 ExprObjectKind &OK,
5734 SourceLocation QuestionLoc) {
5735 // FIXME: Handle C99's complex types, vector types, block pointers and Obj-C++
5736 // interface pointers.
5737
5738 // C++11 [expr.cond]p1
5739 // The first expression is contextually converted to bool.
5740 //
5741 // FIXME; GCC's vector extension permits the use of a?b:c where the type of
5742 // a is that of a integer vector with the same number of elements and
5743 // size as the vectors of b and c. If one of either b or c is a scalar
5744 // it is implicitly converted to match the type of the vector.
5745 // Otherwise the expression is ill-formed. If both b and c are scalars,
5746 // then b and c are checked and converted to the type of a if possible.
5747 // Unlike the OpenCL ?: operator, the expression is evaluated as
5748 // (a[0] != 0 ? b[0] : c[0], .. , a[n] != 0 ? b[n] : c[n]).
5749 if (!Cond.get()->isTypeDependent()) {
5750 ExprResult CondRes = CheckCXXBooleanCondition(Cond.get());
5751 if (CondRes.isInvalid())
5752 return QualType();
5753 Cond = CondRes;
5754 }
5755
5756 // Assume r-value.
5757 VK = VK_RValue;
5758 OK = OK_Ordinary;
5759
5760 // Either of the arguments dependent?
5761 if (LHS.get()->isTypeDependent() || RHS.get()->isTypeDependent())
5762 return Context.DependentTy;
5763
5764 // C++11 [expr.cond]p2
5765 // If either the second or the third operand has type (cv) void, ...
5766 QualType LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
5767 QualType RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
5768 bool LVoid = LTy->isVoidType();
5769 bool RVoid = RTy->isVoidType();
5770 if (LVoid || RVoid) {
5771 // ... one of the following shall hold:
5772 // -- The second or the third operand (but not both) is a (possibly
5773 // parenthesized) throw-expression; the result is of the type
5774 // and value category of the other.
5775 bool LThrow = isa<CXXThrowExpr>(LHS.get()->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
5776 bool RThrow = isa<CXXThrowExpr>(RHS.get()->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
5777 if (LThrow != RThrow) {
5778 Expr *NonThrow = LThrow ? RHS.get() : LHS.get();
5779 VK = NonThrow->getValueKind();
5780 // DR (no number yet): the result is a bit-field if the
5781 // non-throw-expression operand is a bit-field.
5782 OK = NonThrow->getObjectKind();
5783 return NonThrow->getType();
5784 }
5785
5786 // -- Both the second and third operands have type void; the result is of
5787 // type void and is a prvalue.
5788 if (LVoid && RVoid)
5789 return Context.VoidTy;
5790
5791 // Neither holds, error.
5792 Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_void_nonvoid)
5793 << (LVoid ? RTy : LTy) << (LVoid ? 0 : 1)
5794 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5795 return QualType();
5796 }
5797
5798 // Neither is void.
5799
5800 // C++11 [expr.cond]p3
5801 // Otherwise, if the second and third operand have different types, and
5802 // either has (cv) class type [...] an attempt is made to convert each of
5803 // those operands to the type of the other.
5804 if (!Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy) &&
5805 (LTy->isRecordType() || RTy->isRecordType())) {
5806 // These return true if a single direction is already ambiguous.
5807 QualType L2RType, R2LType;
5808 bool HaveL2R, HaveR2L;
5809 if (TryClassUnification(*this, LHS.get(), RHS.get(), QuestionLoc, HaveL2R, L2RType))
5810 return QualType();
5811 if (TryClassUnification(*this, RHS.get(), LHS.get(), QuestionLoc, HaveR2L, R2LType))
5812 return QualType();
5813
5814 // If both can be converted, [...] the program is ill-formed.
5815 if (HaveL2R && HaveR2L) {
5816 Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_ambiguous)
5817 << LTy << RTy << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5818 return QualType();
5819 }
5820
5821 // If exactly one conversion is possible, that conversion is applied to
5822 // the chosen operand and the converted operands are used in place of the
5823 // original operands for the remainder of this section.
5824 if (HaveL2R) {
5825 if (ConvertForConditional(*this, LHS, L2RType) || LHS.isInvalid())
5826 return QualType();
5827 LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
5828 } else if (HaveR2L) {
5829 if (ConvertForConditional(*this, RHS, R2LType) || RHS.isInvalid())
5830 return QualType();
5831 RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
5832 }
5833 }
5834
5835 // C++11 [expr.cond]p3
5836 // if both are glvalues of the same value category and the same type except
5837 // for cv-qualification, an attempt is made to convert each of those
5838 // operands to the type of the other.
5839 // FIXME:
5840 // Resolving a defect in P0012R1: we extend this to cover all cases where
5841 // one of the operands is reference-compatible with the other, in order
5842 // to support conditionals between functions differing in noexcept.
5843 ExprValueKind LVK = LHS.get()->getValueKind();
5844 ExprValueKind RVK = RHS.get()->getValueKind();
5845 if (!Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy) &&
5846 LVK == RVK && LVK != VK_RValue) {
5847 // DerivedToBase was already handled by the class-specific case above.
5848 // FIXME: Should we allow ObjC conversions here?
5849 bool DerivedToBase, ObjCConversion, ObjCLifetimeConversion;
5850 if (CompareReferenceRelationship(
5851 QuestionLoc, LTy, RTy, DerivedToBase,
5852 ObjCConversion, ObjCLifetimeConversion) == Ref_Compatible &&
5853 !DerivedToBase && !ObjCConversion && !ObjCLifetimeConversion &&
5854 // [...] subject to the constraint that the reference must bind
5855 // directly [...]
5856 !RHS.get()->refersToBitField() &&
5857 !RHS.get()->refersToVectorElement()) {
5858 RHS = ImpCastExprToType(RHS.get(), LTy, CK_NoOp, RVK);
5859 RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
5860 } else if (CompareReferenceRelationship(
5861 QuestionLoc, RTy, LTy, DerivedToBase,
5862 ObjCConversion, ObjCLifetimeConversion) == Ref_Compatible &&
5863 !DerivedToBase && !ObjCConversion && !ObjCLifetimeConversion &&
5864 !LHS.get()->refersToBitField() &&
5865 !LHS.get()->refersToVectorElement()) {
5866 LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), RTy, CK_NoOp, LVK);
5867 LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
5868 }
5869 }
5870
5871 // C++11 [expr.cond]p4
5872 // If the second and third operands are glvalues of the same value
5873 // category and have the same type, the result is of that type and
5874 // value category and it is a bit-field if the second or the third
5875 // operand is a bit-field, or if both are bit-fields.
5876 // We only extend this to bitfields, not to the crazy other kinds of
5877 // l-values.
5878 bool Same = Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy);
5879 if (Same && LVK == RVK && LVK != VK_RValue &&
5880 LHS.get()->isOrdinaryOrBitFieldObject() &&
5881 RHS.get()->isOrdinaryOrBitFieldObject()) {
5882 VK = LHS.get()->getValueKind();
5883 if (LHS.get()->getObjectKind() == OK_BitField ||
5884 RHS.get()->getObjectKind() == OK_BitField)
5885 OK = OK_BitField;
5886
5887 // If we have function pointer types, unify them anyway to unify their
5888 // exception specifications, if any.
5889 if (LTy->isFunctionPointerType() || LTy->isMemberFunctionPointerType()) {
5890 Qualifiers Qs = LTy.getQualifiers();
5891 LTy = FindCompositePointerType(QuestionLoc, LHS, RHS,
5892 /*ConvertArgs*/false);
5893 LTy = Context.getQualifiedType(LTy, Qs);
5894
5895 assert(!LTy.isNull() && "failed to find composite pointer type for "
5896 "canonically equivalent function ptr types");
5897 assert(Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy) && "bad composite pointer type");
5898 }
5899
5900 return LTy;
5901 }
5902
5903 // C++11 [expr.cond]p5
5904 // Otherwise, the result is a prvalue. If the second and third operands
5905 // do not have the same type, and either has (cv) class type, ...
5906 if (!Same && (LTy->isRecordType() || RTy->isRecordType())) {
5907 // ... overload resolution is used to determine the conversions (if any)
5908 // to be applied to the operands. If the overload resolution fails, the
5909 // program is ill-formed.
5910 if (FindConditionalOverload(*this, LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc))
5911 return QualType();
5912 }
5913
5914 // C++11 [expr.cond]p6
5915 // Lvalue-to-rvalue, array-to-pointer, and function-to-pointer standard
5916 // conversions are performed on the second and third operands.
5917 LHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(LHS.get());
5918 RHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(RHS.get());
5919 if (LHS.isInvalid() || RHS.isInvalid())
5920 return QualType();
5921 LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
5922 RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
5923
5924 // After those conversions, one of the following shall hold:
5925 // -- The second and third operands have the same type; the result
5926 // is of that type. If the operands have class type, the result
5927 // is a prvalue temporary of the result type, which is
5928 // copy-initialized from either the second operand or the third
5929 // operand depending on the value of the first operand.
5930 if (Context.getCanonicalType(LTy) == Context.getCanonicalType(RTy)) {
5931 if (LTy->isRecordType()) {
5932 // The operands have class type. Make a temporary copy.
5933 InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(LTy);
5934
5935 ExprResult LHSCopy = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity,
5936 SourceLocation(),
5937 LHS);
5938 if (LHSCopy.isInvalid())
5939 return QualType();
5940
5941 ExprResult RHSCopy = PerformCopyInitialization(Entity,
5942 SourceLocation(),
5943 RHS);
5944 if (RHSCopy.isInvalid())
5945 return QualType();
5946
5947 LHS = LHSCopy;
5948 RHS = RHSCopy;
5949 }
5950
5951 // If we have function pointer types, unify them anyway to unify their
5952 // exception specifications, if any.
5953 if (LTy->isFunctionPointerType() || LTy->isMemberFunctionPointerType()) {
5954 LTy = FindCompositePointerType(QuestionLoc, LHS, RHS);
5955 assert(!LTy.isNull() && "failed to find composite pointer type for "
5956 "canonically equivalent function ptr types");
5957 }
5958
5959 return LTy;
5960 }
5961
5962 // Extension: conditional operator involving vector types.
5963 if (LTy->isVectorType() || RTy->isVectorType())
5964 return CheckVectorOperands(LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc, /*isCompAssign*/false,
5965 /*AllowBothBool*/true,
5966 /*AllowBoolConversions*/false);
5967
5968 // -- The second and third operands have arithmetic or enumeration type;
5969 // the usual arithmetic conversions are performed to bring them to a
5970 // common type, and the result is of that type.
5971 if (LTy->isArithmeticType() && RTy->isArithmeticType()) {
5972 QualType ResTy = UsualArithmeticConversions(LHS, RHS);
5973 if (LHS.isInvalid() || RHS.isInvalid())
5974 return QualType();
5975 if (ResTy.isNull()) {
5976 Diag(QuestionLoc,
5977 diag::err_typecheck_cond_incompatible_operands) << LTy << RTy
5978 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
5979 return QualType();
5980 }
5981
5982 LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), ResTy, PrepareScalarCast(LHS, ResTy));
5983 RHS = ImpCastExprToType(RHS.get(), ResTy, PrepareScalarCast(RHS, ResTy));
5984
5985 return ResTy;
5986 }
5987
5988 // -- The second and third operands have pointer type, or one has pointer
5989 // type and the other is a null pointer constant, or both are null
5990 // pointer constants, at least one of which is non-integral; pointer
5991 // conversions and qualification conversions are performed to bring them
5992 // to their composite pointer type. The result is of the composite
5993 // pointer type.
5994 // -- The second and third operands have pointer to member type, or one has
5995 // pointer to member type and the other is a null pointer constant;
5996 // pointer to member conversions and qualification conversions are
5997 // performed to bring them to a common type, whose cv-qualification
5998 // shall match the cv-qualification of either the second or the third
5999 // operand. The result is of the common type.
6000 QualType Composite = FindCompositePointerType(QuestionLoc, LHS, RHS);
6001 if (!Composite.isNull())
6002 return Composite;
6003
6004 // Similarly, attempt to find composite type of two objective-c pointers.
6005 Composite = FindCompositeObjCPointerType(LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc);
6006 if (!Composite.isNull())
6007 return Composite;
6008
6009 // Check if we are using a null with a non-pointer type.
6010 if (DiagnoseConditionalForNull(LHS.get(), RHS.get(), QuestionLoc))
6011 return QualType();
6012
6013 Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_typecheck_cond_incompatible_operands)
6014 << LHS.get()->getType() << RHS.get()->getType()
6015 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6016 return QualType();
6017}
6018
6019static FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo
6020mergeExceptionSpecs(Sema &S, FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo ESI1,
6021 FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo ESI2,
6022 SmallVectorImpl<QualType> &ExceptionTypeStorage) {
6023 ExceptionSpecificationType EST1 = ESI1.Type;
6024 ExceptionSpecificationType EST2 = ESI2.Type;
6025
6026 // If either of them can throw anything, that is the result.
6027 if (EST1 == EST_None) return ESI1;
6028 if (EST2 == EST_None) return ESI2;
6029 if (EST1 == EST_MSAny) return ESI1;
6030 if (EST2 == EST_MSAny) return ESI2;
6031 if (EST1 == EST_NoexceptFalse) return ESI1;
6032 if (EST2 == EST_NoexceptFalse) return ESI2;
6033
6034 // If either of them is non-throwing, the result is the other.
6035 if (EST1 == EST_NoThrow) return ESI2;
6036 if (EST2 == EST_NoThrow) return ESI1;
6037 if (EST1 == EST_DynamicNone) return ESI2;
6038 if (EST2 == EST_DynamicNone) return ESI1;
6039 if (EST1 == EST_BasicNoexcept) return ESI2;
6040 if (EST2 == EST_BasicNoexcept) return ESI1;
6041 if (EST1 == EST_NoexceptTrue) return ESI2;
6042 if (EST2 == EST_NoexceptTrue) return ESI1;
6043
6044 // If we're left with value-dependent computed noexcept expressions, we're
6045 // stuck. Before C++17, we can just drop the exception specification entirely,
6046 // since it's not actually part of the canonical type. And this should never
6047 // happen in C++17, because it would mean we were computing the composite
6048 // pointer type of dependent types, which should never happen.
6049 if (EST1 == EST_DependentNoexcept || EST2 == EST_DependentNoexcept) {
6050 assert(!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
6051 "computing composite pointer type of dependent types");
6052 return FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo();
6053 }
6054
6055 // Switch over the possibilities so that people adding new values know to
6056 // update this function.
6057 switch (EST1) {
6058 case EST_None:
6059 case EST_DynamicNone:
6060 case EST_MSAny:
6061 case EST_BasicNoexcept:
6062 case EST_DependentNoexcept:
6063 case EST_NoexceptFalse:
6064 case EST_NoexceptTrue:
6065 case EST_NoThrow:
6066 llvm_unreachable("handled above");
6067
6068 case EST_Dynamic: {
6069 // This is the fun case: both exception specifications are dynamic. Form
6070 // the union of the two lists.
6071 assert(EST2 == EST_Dynamic && "other cases should already be handled");
6072 llvm::SmallPtrSet<QualType, 8> Found;
6073 for (auto &Exceptions : {ESI1.Exceptions, ESI2.Exceptions})
6074 for (QualType E : Exceptions)
6075 if (Found.insert(S.Context.getCanonicalType(E)).second)
6076 ExceptionTypeStorage.push_back(E);
6077
6078 FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo Result(EST_Dynamic);
6079 Result.Exceptions = ExceptionTypeStorage;
6080 return Result;
6081 }
6082
6083 case EST_Unevaluated:
6084 case EST_Uninstantiated:
6085 case EST_Unparsed:
6086 llvm_unreachable("shouldn't see unresolved exception specifications here");
6087 }
6088
6089 llvm_unreachable("invalid ExceptionSpecificationType");
6090}
6091
6092/// Find a merged pointer type and convert the two expressions to it.
6093///
6094/// This finds the composite pointer type (or member pointer type) for @p E1
6095/// and @p E2 according to C++1z 5p14. It converts both expressions to this
6096/// type and returns it.
6097/// It does not emit diagnostics.
6098///
6099/// \param Loc The location of the operator requiring these two expressions to
6100/// be converted to the composite pointer type.
6101///
6102/// \param ConvertArgs If \c false, do not convert E1 and E2 to the target type.
6103QualType Sema::FindCompositePointerType(SourceLocation Loc,
6104 Expr *&E1, Expr *&E2,
6105 bool ConvertArgs) {
6106 assert(getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && "This function assumes C++");
6107
6108 // C++1z [expr]p14:
6109 // The composite pointer type of two operands p1 and p2 having types T1
6110 // and T2
6111 QualType T1 = E1->getType(), T2 = E2->getType();
6112
6113 // where at least one is a pointer or pointer to member type or
6114 // std::nullptr_t is:
6115 bool T1IsPointerLike = T1->isAnyPointerType() || T1->isMemberPointerType() ||
6116 T1->isNullPtrType();
6117 bool T2IsPointerLike = T2->isAnyPointerType() || T2->isMemberPointerType() ||
6118 T2->isNullPtrType();
6119 if (!T1IsPointerLike && !T2IsPointerLike)
6120 return QualType();
6121
6122 // - if both p1 and p2 are null pointer constants, std::nullptr_t;
6123 // This can't actually happen, following the standard, but we also use this
6124 // to implement the end of [expr.conv], which hits this case.
6125 //
6126 // - if either p1 or p2 is a null pointer constant, T2 or T1, respectively;
6127 if (T1IsPointerLike &&
