6128 E2->isNullPointerConstant(Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull)) {
6129 if (ConvertArgs)
6130 E2 = ImpCastExprToType(E2, T1, T1->isMemberPointerType()
6131 ? CK_NullToMemberPointer
6132 : CK_NullToPointer).get();
6133 return T1;
6134 }
6135 if (T2IsPointerLike &&
6136 E1->isNullPointerConstant(Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull)) {
6137 if (ConvertArgs)
6138 E1 = ImpCastExprToType(E1, T2, T2->isMemberPointerType()
6139 ? CK_NullToMemberPointer
6140 : CK_NullToPointer).get();
6141 return T2;
6142 }
6143
6144 // Now both have to be pointers or member pointers.
6145 if (!T1IsPointerLike || !T2IsPointerLike)
6146 return QualType();
6147 assert(!T1->isNullPtrType() && !T2->isNullPtrType() &&
6148 "nullptr_t should be a null pointer constant");
6149
6150 // - if T1 or T2 is "pointer to cv1 void" and the other type is
6151 // "pointer to cv2 T", "pointer to cv12 void", where cv12 is
6152 // the union of cv1 and cv2;
6153 // - if T1 or T2 is "pointer to noexcept function" and the other type is
6154 // "pointer to function", where the function types are otherwise the same,
6155 // "pointer to function";
6156 // FIXME: This rule is defective: it should also permit removing noexcept
6157 // from a pointer to member function. As a Clang extension, we also
6158 // permit removing 'noreturn', so we generalize this rule to;
6159 // - [Clang] If T1 and T2 are both of type "pointer to function" or
6160 // "pointer to member function" and the pointee types can be unified
6161 // by a function pointer conversion, that conversion is applied
6162 // before checking the following rules.
6163 // - if T1 is "pointer to cv1 C1" and T2 is "pointer to cv2 C2", where C1
6164 // is reference-related to C2 or C2 is reference-related to C1 (8.6.3),
6165 // the cv-combined type of T1 and T2 or the cv-combined type of T2 and T1,
6166 // respectively;
6167 // - if T1 is "pointer to member of C1 of type cv1 U1" and T2 is "pointer
6168 // to member of C2 of type cv2 U2" where C1 is reference-related to C2 or
6169 // C2 is reference-related to C1 (8.6.3), the cv-combined type of T2 and
6170 // T1 or the cv-combined type of T1 and T2, respectively;
6171 // - if T1 and T2 are similar types (4.5), the cv-combined type of T1 and
6172 // T2;
6173 //
6174 // If looked at in the right way, these bullets all do the same thing.
6175 // What we do here is, we build the two possible cv-combined types, and try
6176 // the conversions in both directions. If only one works, or if the two
6177 // composite types are the same, we have succeeded.
6178 // FIXME: extended qualifiers?
6179 //
6180 // Note that this will fail to find a composite pointer type for "pointer
6181 // to void" and "pointer to function". We can't actually perform the final
6182 // conversion in this case, even though a composite pointer type formally
6183 // exists.
6184 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> QualifierUnion;
6185 SmallVector<std::pair<const Type *, const Type *>, 4> MemberOfClass;
6186 QualType Composite1 = T1;
6187 QualType Composite2 = T2;
6188 unsigned NeedConstBefore = 0;
6189 while (true) {
6190 const PointerType *Ptr1, *Ptr2;
6191 if ((Ptr1 = Composite1->getAs<PointerType>()) &&
6192 (Ptr2 = Composite2->getAs<PointerType>())) {
6193 Composite1 = Ptr1->getPointeeType();
6194 Composite2 = Ptr2->getPointeeType();
6195
6196 // If we're allowed to create a non-standard composite type, keep track
6197 // of where we need to fill in additional 'const' qualifiers.
6198 if (Composite1.getCVRQualifiers() != Composite2.getCVRQualifiers())
6199 NeedConstBefore = QualifierUnion.size();
6200
6201 QualifierUnion.push_back(
6202 Composite1.getCVRQualifiers() | Composite2.getCVRQualifiers());
6203 MemberOfClass.push_back(std::make_pair(nullptr, nullptr));
6204 continue;
6205 }
6206
6207 const MemberPointerType *MemPtr1, *MemPtr2;
6208 if ((MemPtr1 = Composite1->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) &&
6209 (MemPtr2 = Composite2->getAs<MemberPointerType>())) {
6210 Composite1 = MemPtr1->getPointeeType();
6211 Composite2 = MemPtr2->getPointeeType();
6212
6213 // If we're allowed to create a non-standard composite type, keep track
6214 // of where we need to fill in additional 'const' qualifiers.
6215 if (Composite1.getCVRQualifiers() != Composite2.getCVRQualifiers())
6216 NeedConstBefore = QualifierUnion.size();
6217
6218 QualifierUnion.push_back(
6219 Composite1.getCVRQualifiers() | Composite2.getCVRQualifiers());
6220 MemberOfClass.push_back(std::make_pair(MemPtr1->getClass(),
6221 MemPtr2->getClass()));
6222 continue;
6223 }
6224
6225 // FIXME: block pointer types?
6226
6227 // Cannot unwrap any more types.
6228 break;
6229 }
6230
6231 // Apply the function pointer conversion to unify the types. We've already
6232 // unwrapped down to the function types, and we want to merge rather than
6233 // just convert, so do this ourselves rather than calling
6234 // IsFunctionConversion.
6235 //
6236 // FIXME: In order to match the standard wording as closely as possible, we
6237 // currently only do this under a single level of pointers. Ideally, we would
6238 // allow this in general, and set NeedConstBefore to the relevant depth on
6239 // the side(s) where we changed anything.
6240 if (QualifierUnion.size() == 1) {
6241 if (auto *FPT1 = Composite1->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
6242 if (auto *FPT2 = Composite2->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
6243 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI1 = FPT1->getExtProtoInfo();
6244 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI2 = FPT2->getExtProtoInfo();
6245
6246 // The result is noreturn if both operands are.
6247 bool Noreturn =
6248 EPI1.ExtInfo.getNoReturn() && EPI2.ExtInfo.getNoReturn();
6249 EPI1.ExtInfo = EPI1.ExtInfo.withNoReturn(Noreturn);
6250 EPI2.ExtInfo = EPI2.ExtInfo.withNoReturn(Noreturn);
6251
6252 // The result is nothrow if both operands are.
6253 SmallVector<QualType, 8> ExceptionTypeStorage;
6254 EPI1.ExceptionSpec = EPI2.ExceptionSpec =
6255 mergeExceptionSpecs(*this, EPI1.ExceptionSpec, EPI2.ExceptionSpec,
6256 ExceptionTypeStorage);
6257
6258 Composite1 = Context.getFunctionType(FPT1->getReturnType(),
6259 FPT1->getParamTypes(), EPI1);
6260 Composite2 = Context.getFunctionType(FPT2->getReturnType(),
6261 FPT2->getParamTypes(), EPI2);
6262 }
6263 }
6264 }
6265
6266 if (NeedConstBefore) {
6267 // Extension: Add 'const' to qualifiers that come before the first qualifier
6268 // mismatch, so that our (non-standard!) composite type meets the
6269 // requirements of C++ [conv.qual]p4 bullet 3.
6270 for (unsigned I = 0; I != NeedConstBefore; ++I)
6271 if ((QualifierUnion[I] & Qualifiers::Const) == 0)
6272 QualifierUnion[I] = QualifierUnion[I] | Qualifiers::Const;
6273 }
6274
6275 // Rewrap the composites as pointers or member pointers with the union CVRs.
6276 auto MOC = MemberOfClass.rbegin();
6277 for (unsigned CVR : llvm::reverse(QualifierUnion)) {
6278 Qualifiers Quals = Qualifiers::fromCVRMask(CVR);
6279 auto Classes = *MOC++;
6280 if (Classes.first && Classes.second) {
6281 // Rebuild member pointer type
6282 Composite1 = Context.getMemberPointerType(
6283 Context.getQualifiedType(Composite1, Quals), Classes.first);
6284 Composite2 = Context.getMemberPointerType(
6285 Context.getQualifiedType(Composite2, Quals), Classes.second);
6286 } else {
6287 // Rebuild pointer type
6288 Composite1 =
6289 Context.getPointerType(Context.getQualifiedType(Composite1, Quals));
6290 Composite2 =
6291 Context.getPointerType(Context.getQualifiedType(Composite2, Quals));
6292 }
6293 }
6294
6295 struct Conversion {
6296 Sema &S;
6297 Expr *&E1, *&E2;
6298 QualType Composite;
6299 InitializedEntity Entity;
6300 InitializationKind Kind;
6301 InitializationSequence E1ToC, E2ToC;
6302 bool Viable;
6303
6304 Conversion(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, Expr *&E1, Expr *&E2,
6305 QualType Composite)
6306 : S(S), E1(E1), E2(E2), Composite(Composite),
6307 Entity(InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(Composite)),
6308 Kind(InitializationKind::CreateCopy(Loc, SourceLocation())),
6309 E1ToC(S, Entity, Kind, E1), E2ToC(S, Entity, Kind, E2),
6310 Viable(E1ToC && E2ToC) {}
6311
6312 bool perform() {
6313 ExprResult E1Result = E1ToC.Perform(S, Entity, Kind, E1);
6314 if (E1Result.isInvalid())
6315 return true;
6316 E1 = E1Result.getAs<Expr>();
6317
6318 ExprResult E2Result = E2ToC.Perform(S, Entity, Kind, E2);
6319 if (E2Result.isInvalid())
6320 return true;
6321 E2 = E2Result.getAs<Expr>();
6322
6323 return false;
6324 }
6325 };
6326
6327 // Try to convert to each composite pointer type.
6328 Conversion C1(*this, Loc, E1, E2, Composite1);
6329 if (C1.Viable && Context.hasSameType(Composite1, Composite2)) {
6330 if (ConvertArgs && C1.perform())
6331 return QualType();
6332 return C1.Composite;
6333 }
6334 Conversion C2(*this, Loc, E1, E2, Composite2);
6335
6336 if (C1.Viable == C2.Viable) {
6337 // Either Composite1 and Composite2 are viable and are different, or
6338 // neither is viable.
6339 // FIXME: How both be viable and different?
6340 return QualType();
6341 }
6342
6343 // Convert to the chosen type.
6344 if (ConvertArgs && (C1.Viable ? C1 : C2).perform())
6345 return QualType();
6346
6347 return C1.Viable ? C1.Composite : C2.Composite;
6348}
6349
6350ExprResult Sema::MaybeBindToTemporary(Expr *E) {
6351 if (!E)
6352 return ExprError();
6353
6354 assert(!isa<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E) && "Double-bound temporary?");
6355
6356 // If the result is a glvalue, we shouldn't bind it.
6357 if (!E->isRValue())
6358 return E;
6359
6360 // In ARC, calls that return a retainable type can return retained,
6361 // in which case we have to insert a consuming cast.
6362 if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
6363 E->getType()->isObjCRetainableType()) {
6364
6365 bool ReturnsRetained;
6366
6367 // For actual calls, we compute this by examining the type of the
6368 // called value.
6369 if (CallExpr *Call = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(E)) {
6370 Expr *Callee = Call->getCallee()->IgnoreParens();
6371 QualType T = Callee->getType();
6372
6373 if (T == Context.BoundMemberTy) {
6374 // Handle pointer-to-members.
6375 if (BinaryOperator *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Callee))
6376 T = BinOp->getRHS()->getType();
6377 else if (MemberExpr *Mem = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Callee))
6378 T = Mem->getMemberDecl()->getType();
6379 }
6380
6381 if (const PointerType *Ptr = T->getAs<PointerType>())
6382 T = Ptr->getPointeeType();
6383 else if (const BlockPointerType *Ptr = T->getAs<BlockPointerType>())
6384 T = Ptr->getPointeeType();
6385 else if (const MemberPointerType *MemPtr = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
6386 T = MemPtr->getPointeeType();
6387
6388 const FunctionType *FTy = T->getAs<FunctionType>();
6389 assert(FTy && "call to value not of function type?");
6390 ReturnsRetained = FTy->getExtInfo().getProducesResult();
6391
6392 // ActOnStmtExpr arranges things so that StmtExprs of retainable
6393 // type always produce a +1 object.
6394 } else if (isa<StmtExpr>(E)) {
6395 ReturnsRetained = true;
6396
6397 // We hit this case with the lambda conversion-to-block optimization;
6398 // we don't want any extra casts here.
6399 } else if (isa<CastExpr>(E) &&
6400 isa<BlockExpr>(cast<CastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr())) {
6401 return E;
6402
6403 // For message sends and property references, we try to find an
6404 // actual method. FIXME: we should infer retention by selector in
6405 // cases where we don't have an actual method.
6406 } else {
6407 ObjCMethodDecl *D = nullptr;
6408 if (ObjCMessageExpr *Send = dyn_cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E)) {
6409 D = Send->getMethodDecl();
6410 } else if (ObjCBoxedExpr *BoxedExpr = dyn_cast<ObjCBoxedExpr>(E)) {
6411 D = BoxedExpr->getBoxingMethod();
6412 } else if (ObjCArrayLiteral *ArrayLit = dyn_cast<ObjCArrayLiteral>(E)) {
6413 // Don't do reclaims if we're using the zero-element array
6414 // constant.
6415 if (ArrayLit->getNumElements() == 0 &&
6416 Context.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.hasEmptyCollections())
6417 return E;
6418
6419 D = ArrayLit->getArrayWithObjectsMethod();
6420 } else if (ObjCDictionaryLiteral *DictLit
6421 = dyn_cast<ObjCDictionaryLiteral>(E)) {
6422 // Don't do reclaims if we're using the zero-element dictionary
6423 // constant.
6424 if (DictLit->getNumElements() == 0 &&
6425 Context.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.hasEmptyCollections())
6426 return E;
6427
6428 D = DictLit->getDictWithObjectsMethod();
6429 }
6430
6431 ReturnsRetained = (D && D->hasAttr<NSReturnsRetainedAttr>());
6432
6433 // Don't do reclaims on performSelector calls; despite their
6434 // return type, the invoked method doesn't necessarily actually
6435 // return an object.
6436 if (!ReturnsRetained &&
6437 D && D->getMethodFamily() == OMF_performSelector)
6438 return E;
6439 }
6440
6441 // Don't reclaim an object of Class type.
6442 if (!ReturnsRetained && E->getType()->isObjCARCImplicitlyUnretainedType())
6443 return E;
6444
6445 Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
6446
6447 CastKind ck = (ReturnsRetained ? CK_ARCConsumeObject
6448 : CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject);
6449 return ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Context, E->getType(), ck, E, nullptr,
6450 VK_RValue);
6451 }
6452
6453 if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
6454 return E;
6455
6456 // Search for the base element type (cf. ASTContext::getBaseElementType) with
6457 // a fast path for the common case that the type is directly a RecordType.
6458 const Type *T = Context.getCanonicalType(E->getType().getTypePtr());
6459 const RecordType *RT = nullptr;
6460 while (!RT) {
6461 switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
6462 case Type::Record:
6463 RT = cast<RecordType>(T);
6464 break;
6465 case Type::ConstantArray:
6466 case Type::IncompleteArray:
6467 case Type::VariableArray:
6468 case Type::DependentSizedArray:
6469 T = cast<ArrayType>(T)->getElementType().getTypePtr();
6470 break;
6471 default:
6472 return E;
6473 }
6474 }
6475
6476 // That should be enough to guarantee that this type is complete, if we're
6477 // not processing a decltype expression.
6478 CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
6479 if (RD->isInvalidDecl() || RD->isDependentContext())
6480 return E;
6481
6482 bool IsDecltype = ExprEvalContexts.back().ExprContext ==
6483 ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Decltype;
6484 CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = IsDecltype ? nullptr : LookupDestructor(RD);
6485
6486 if (Destructor) {
6487 MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getExprLoc(), Destructor);
6488 CheckDestructorAccess(E->getExprLoc(), Destructor,
6489 PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_temp)
6490 << E->getType());
6491 if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, E->getExprLoc()))
6492 return ExprError();
6493
6494 // If destructor is trivial, we can avoid the extra copy.
6495 if (Destructor->isTrivial())
6496 return E;
6497
6498 // We need a cleanup, but we don't need to remember the temporary.
6499 Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
6500 }
6501
6502 CXXTemporary *Temp = CXXTemporary::Create(Context, Destructor);
6503 CXXBindTemporaryExpr *Bind = CXXBindTemporaryExpr::Create(Context, Temp, E);
6504
6505 if (IsDecltype)
6506 ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeBinds.push_back(Bind);
6507
6508 return Bind;
6509}
6510
6511ExprResult
6512Sema::MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(ExprResult SubExpr) {
6513 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
6514 return ExprError();
6515
6516 return MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(SubExpr.get());
6517}
6518
6519Expr *Sema::MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(Expr *SubExpr) {
6520 assert(SubExpr && "subexpression can't be null!");
6521
6522 CleanupVarDeclMarking();
6523
6524 unsigned FirstCleanup = ExprEvalContexts.back().NumCleanupObjects;
6525 assert(ExprCleanupObjects.size() >= FirstCleanup);
6526 assert(Cleanup.exprNeedsCleanups() ||
6527 ExprCleanupObjects.size() == FirstCleanup);
6528 if (!Cleanup.exprNeedsCleanups())
6529 return SubExpr;
6530
6531 auto Cleanups = llvm::makeArrayRef(ExprCleanupObjects.begin() + FirstCleanup,
6532 ExprCleanupObjects.size() - FirstCleanup);
6533
6534 auto *E = ExprWithCleanups::Create(
6535 Context, SubExpr, Cleanup.cleanupsHaveSideEffects(), Cleanups);
6536 DiscardCleanupsInEvaluationContext();
6537
6538 return E;
6539}
6540
6541Stmt *Sema::MaybeCreateStmtWithCleanups(Stmt *SubStmt) {
6542 assert(SubStmt && "sub-statement can't be null!");
6543
6544 CleanupVarDeclMarking();
6545
6546 if (!Cleanup.exprNeedsCleanups())
6547 return SubStmt;
6548
6549 // FIXME: In order to attach the temporaries, wrap the statement into
6550 // a StmtExpr; currently this is only used for asm statements.
6551 // This is hacky, either create a new CXXStmtWithTemporaries statement or
6552 // a new AsmStmtWithTemporaries.
6553 CompoundStmt *CompStmt = CompoundStmt::Create(
6554 Context, SubStmt, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation());
6555 Expr *E = new (Context) StmtExpr(CompStmt, Context.VoidTy, SourceLocation(),
6556 SourceLocation());
6557 return MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(E);
6558}
6559
6560/// Process the expression contained within a decltype. For such expressions,
6561/// certain semantic checks on temporaries are delayed until this point, and
6562/// are omitted for the 'topmost' call in the decltype expression. If the
6563/// topmost call bound a temporary, strip that temporary off the expression.
6564ExprResult Sema::ActOnDecltypeExpression(Expr *E) {
6565 assert(ExprEvalContexts.back().ExprContext ==
6566 ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Decltype &&
6567 "not in a decltype expression");
6568
6569 ExprResult Result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(E);
6570 if (Result.isInvalid())
6571 return ExprError();
6572 E = Result.get();
6573
6574 // C++11 [expr.call]p11:
6575 // If a function call is a prvalue of object type,
6576 // -- if the function call is either
6577 // -- the operand of a decltype-specifier, or
6578 // -- the right operand of a comma operator that is the operand of a
6579 // decltype-specifier,
6580 // a temporary object is not introduced for the prvalue.
6581
6582 // Recursively rebuild ParenExprs and comma expressions to strip out the
6583 // outermost CXXBindTemporaryExpr, if any.
6584 if (ParenExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
6585 ExprResult SubExpr = ActOnDecltypeExpression(PE->getSubExpr());
6586 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
6587 return ExprError();
6588 if (SubExpr.get() == PE->getSubExpr())
6589 return E;
6590 return ActOnParenExpr(PE->getLParen(), PE->getRParen(), SubExpr.get());
6591 }
6592 if (BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
6593 if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
6594 ExprResult RHS = ActOnDecltypeExpression(BO->getRHS());
6595 if (RHS.isInvalid())
6596 return ExprError();
6597 if (RHS.get() == BO->getRHS())
6598 return E;
6599 return new (Context) BinaryOperator(
6600 BO->getLHS(), RHS.get(), BO_Comma, BO->getType(), BO->getValueKind(),
6601 BO->getObjectKind(), BO->getOperatorLoc(), BO->getFPFeatures());
6602 }
6603 }
6604
6605 CXXBindTemporaryExpr *TopBind = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E);
6606 CallExpr *TopCall = TopBind ? dyn_cast<CallExpr>(TopBind->getSubExpr())
6607 : nullptr;
6608 if (TopCall)
6609 E = TopCall;
6610 else
6611 TopBind = nullptr;
6612
6613 // Disable the special decltype handling now.
6614 ExprEvalContexts.back().ExprContext =
6615 ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Other;
6616
6617 // In MS mode, don't perform any extra checking of call return types within a
6618 // decltype expression.
6619 if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat)
6620 return E;
6621
6622 // Perform the semantic checks we delayed until this point.
6623 for (unsigned I = 0, N = ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeCalls.size();
6624 I != N; ++I) {
6625 CallExpr *Call = ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeCalls[I];
6626 if (Call == TopCall)
6627 continue;
6628
6629 if (CheckCallReturnType(Call->getCallReturnType(Context),
6630 Call->getBeginLoc(), Call, Call->getDirectCallee()))
6631 return ExprError();
6632 }
6633
6634 // Now all relevant types are complete, check the destructors are accessible
6635 // and non-deleted, and annotate them on the temporaries.
6636 for (unsigned I = 0, N = ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeBinds.size();
6637 I != N; ++I) {
6638 CXXBindTemporaryExpr *Bind =
6639 ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeBinds[I];
6640 if (Bind == TopBind)
6641 continue;
6642
6643 CXXTemporary *Temp = Bind->getTemporary();
6644
6645 CXXRecordDecl *RD =
6646 Bind->getType()->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
6647 CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = LookupDestructor(RD);
6648 Temp->setDestructor(Destructor);
6649
6650 MarkFunctionReferenced(Bind->getExprLoc(), Destructor);
6651 CheckDestructorAccess(Bind->getExprLoc(), Destructor,
6652 PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_temp)
6653 << Bind->getType());
6654 if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, Bind->getExprLoc()))
6655 return ExprError();
6656
6657 // We need a cleanup, but we don't need to remember the temporary.
6658 Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
6659 }
6660
6661 // Possibly strip off the top CXXBindTemporaryExpr.
6662 return E;
6663}
6664
6665/// Note a set of 'operator->' functions that were used for a member access.
6666static void noteOperatorArrows(Sema &S,
6667 ArrayRef<FunctionDecl *> OperatorArrows) {
6668 unsigned SkipStart = OperatorArrows.size(), SkipCount = 0;
6669 // FIXME: Make this configurable?
6670 unsigned Limit = 9;
6671 if (OperatorArrows.size() > Limit) {
6672 // Produce Limit-1 normal notes and one 'skipping' note.
6673 SkipStart = (Limit - 1) / 2 + (Limit - 1) % 2;
6674 SkipCount = OperatorArrows.size() - (Limit - 1);
6675 }
6676
6677 for (unsigned I = 0; I < OperatorArrows.size(); /**/) {
6678 if (I == SkipStart) {
6679 S.Diag(OperatorArrows[I]->getLocation(),
6680 diag::note_operator_arrows_suppressed)
6681 << SkipCount;
6682 I += SkipCount;
6683 } else {
6684 S.Diag(OperatorArrows[I]->getLocation(), diag::note_operator_arrow_here)
6685 << OperatorArrows[I]->getCallResultType();
6686 ++I;
6687 }
6688 }
6689}
6690
6691ExprResult Sema::ActOnStartCXXMemberReference(Scope *S, Expr *Base,
6692 SourceLocation OpLoc,
6693 tok::TokenKind OpKind,
6694 ParsedType &ObjectType,
6695 bool &MayBePseudoDestructor) {
6696 // Since this might be a postfix expression, get rid of ParenListExprs.
6697 ExprResult Result = MaybeConvertParenListExprToParenExpr(S, Base);
6698 if (Result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
6699 Base = Result.get();
6700
6701 Result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(Base);
6702 if (Result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
6703 Base = Result.get();
6704
6705 QualType BaseType = Base->getType();
6706 MayBePseudoDestructor = false;
6707 if (BaseType->isDependentType()) {
6708 // If we have a pointer to a dependent type and are using the -> operator,
6709 // the object type is the type that the pointer points to. We might still
6710 // have enough information about that type to do something useful.
6711 if (OpKind == tok::arrow)
6712 if (const PointerType *Ptr = BaseType->getAs<PointerType>())
6713 BaseType = Ptr->getPointeeType();
6714
6715 ObjectType = ParsedType::make(BaseType);
6716 MayBePseudoDestructor = true;
6717 return Base;
6718 }
6719
6720 // C++ [over.match.oper]p8:
6721 // [...] When operator->returns, the operator-> is applied to the value
6722 // returned, with the original second operand.
6723 if (OpKind == tok::arrow) {
6724 QualType StartingType = BaseType;
6725 bool NoArrowOperatorFound = false;
6726 bool FirstIteration = true;
6727 FunctionDecl *CurFD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CurContext);
6728 // The set of types we've considered so far.
6729 llvm::SmallPtrSet<CanQualType,8> CTypes;
6730 SmallVector<FunctionDecl*, 8> OperatorArrows;
6731 CTypes.insert(Context.getCanonicalType(BaseType));
6732
6733 while (BaseType->isRecordType()) {
6734 if (OperatorArrows.size() >= getLangOpts().ArrowDepth) {
6735 Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_operator_arrow_depth_exceeded)
6736 << StartingType << getLangOpts().ArrowDepth << Base->getSourceRange();
6737 noteOperatorArrows(*this, OperatorArrows);
6738 Diag(OpLoc, diag::note_operator_arrow_depth)
6739 << getLangOpts().ArrowDepth;
6740 return ExprError();
6741 }
6742
6743 Result = BuildOverloadedArrowExpr(
6744 S, Base, OpLoc,
6745 // When in a template specialization and on the first loop iteration,
6746 // potentially give the default diagnostic (with the fixit in a
6747 // separate note) instead of having the error reported back to here
6748 // and giving a diagnostic with a fixit attached to the error itself.
6749 (FirstIteration && CurFD && CurFD->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization())
6750 ? nullptr
6751 : &NoArrowOperatorFound);
6752 if (Result.isInvalid()) {
6753 if (NoArrowOperatorFound) {
6754 if (FirstIteration) {
6755 Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_suggestion)
6756 << BaseType << 1 << Base->getSourceRange()
6757 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OpLoc, ".");
6758 OpKind = tok::period;
6759 break;
6760 }
6761 Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_arrow)
6762 << BaseType << Base->getSourceRange();
6763 CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(Base);
6764 if (Decl *CD = (CE ? CE->getCalleeDecl() : nullptr)) {
6765 Diag(CD->getBeginLoc(),
6766 diag::note_member_reference_arrow_from_operator_arrow);
6767 }
6768 }
6769 return ExprError();
6770 }
6771 Base = Result.get();
6772 if (CXXOperatorCallExpr *OpCall = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(Base))
6773 OperatorArrows.push_back(OpCall->getDirectCallee());
6774 BaseType = Base->getType();
6775 CanQualType CBaseType = Context.getCanonicalType(BaseType);
6776 if (!CTypes.insert(CBaseType).second) {
6777 Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_operator_arrow_circular) << StartingType;
6778 noteOperatorArrows(*this, OperatorArrows);
6779 return ExprError();
6780 }
6781 FirstIteration = false;
6782 }
6783
6784 if (OpKind == tok::arrow) {
6785 if (BaseType->isPointerType())
6786 BaseType = BaseType->getPointeeType();
6787 else if (auto *AT = Context.getAsArrayType(BaseType))
6788 BaseType = AT->getElementType();
6789 }
6790 }
6791
6792 // Objective-C properties allow "." access on Objective-C pointer types,
6793 // so adjust the base type to the object type itself.
6794 if (BaseType->isObjCObjectPointerType())
6795 BaseType = BaseType->getPointeeType();
6796
6797 // C++ [basic.lookup.classref]p2:
6798 // [...] If the type of the object expression is of pointer to scalar
6799 // type, the unqualified-id is looked up in the context of the complete
6800 // postfix-expression.
6801 //
6802 // This also indicates that we could be parsing a pseudo-destructor-name.
6803 // Note that Objective-C class and object types can be pseudo-destructor
6804 // expressions or normal member (ivar or property) access expressions, and
6805 // it's legal for the type to be incomplete if this is a pseudo-destructor
6806 // call. We'll do more incomplete-type checks later in the lookup process,
6807 // so just skip this check for ObjC types.
6808 if (BaseType->isObjCObjectOrInterfaceType()) {
6809 ObjectType = ParsedType::make(BaseType);
6810 MayBePseudoDestructor = true;
6811 return Base;
6812 } else if (!BaseType->isRecordType()) {
6813 ObjectType = nullptr;
6814 MayBePseudoDestructor = true;
6815 return Base;
6816 }
6817
6818 // The object type must be complete (or dependent), or
6819 // C++11 [expr.prim.general]p3:
6820 // Unlike the object expression in other contexts, *this is not required to
6821 // be of complete type for purposes of class member access (5.2.5) outside
6822 // the member function body.
6823 if (!BaseType->isDependentType() &&
6824 !isThisOutsideMemberFunctionBody(BaseType) &&
6825 RequireCompleteType(OpLoc, BaseType, diag::err_incomplete_member_access))
6826 return ExprError();
6827
6828 // C++ [basic.lookup.classref]p2:
6829 // If the id-expression in a class member access (5.2.5) is an
6830 // unqualified-id, and the type of the object expression is of a class
6831 // type C (or of pointer to a class type C), the unqualified-id is looked
6832 // up in the scope of class C. [...]
6833 ObjectType = ParsedType::make(BaseType);
6834 return Base;
6835}
6836
6837static bool CheckArrow(Sema& S, QualType& ObjectType, Expr *&Base,
6838 tok::TokenKind& OpKind, SourceLocation OpLoc) {
6839 if (Base->hasPlaceholderType()) {
6840 ExprResult result = S.CheckPlaceholderExpr(Base);
6841 if (result.isInvalid()) return true;
6842 Base = result.get();
6843 }
6844 ObjectType = Base->getType();
6845
6846 // C++ [expr.pseudo]p2:
6847 // The left-hand side of the dot operator shall be of scalar type. The
6848 // left-hand side of the arrow operator shall be of pointer to scalar type.
6849 // This scalar type is the object type.
6850 // Note that this is rather different from the normal handling for the
6851 // arrow operator.
6852 if (OpKind == tok::arrow) {
6853 if (const PointerType *Ptr = ObjectType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
6854 ObjectType = Ptr->getPointeeType();
6855 } else if (!Base->isTypeDependent()) {
6856 // The user wrote "p->" when they probably meant "p."; fix it.
6857 S.Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_suggestion)
6858 << ObjectType << true
6859 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OpLoc, ".");
6860 if (S.isSFINAEContext())
6861 return true;
6862
6863 OpKind = tok::period;
6864 }
6865 }
6866
6867 return false;
6868}
6869
6870/// Check if it's ok to try and recover dot pseudo destructor calls on
6871/// pointer objects.
6872static bool
6873canRecoverDotPseudoDestructorCallsOnPointerObjects(Sema &SemaRef,
6874 QualType DestructedType) {
6875 // If this is a record type, check if its destructor is callable.
6876 if (auto *RD = DestructedType->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
6877 if (RD->hasDefinition())
6878 if (CXXDestructorDecl *D = SemaRef.LookupDestructor(RD))
6879 return SemaRef.CanUseDecl(D, /*TreatUnavailableAsInvalid=*/false);
6880 return false;
6881 }
6882
6883 // Otherwise, check if it's a type for which it's valid to use a pseudo-dtor.
6884 return DestructedType->isDependentType() || DestructedType->isScalarType() ||
6885 DestructedType->isVectorType();
6886}
6887
6888ExprResult Sema::BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(Expr *Base,
6889 SourceLocation OpLoc,
6890 tok::TokenKind OpKind,
6891 const CXXScopeSpec &SS,
6892 TypeSourceInfo *ScopeTypeInfo,
6893 SourceLocation CCLoc,
6894 SourceLocation TildeLoc,
6895 PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destructed) {
6896 TypeSourceInfo *DestructedTypeInfo = Destructed.getTypeSourceInfo();
6897
6898 QualType ObjectType;
6899 if (CheckArrow(*this, ObjectType, Base, OpKind, OpLoc))
6900 return ExprError();
6901
6902 if (!ObjectType->isDependentType() && !ObjectType->isScalarType() &&
6903 !ObjectType->isVectorType()) {
6904 if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && ObjectType->isVoidType())
6905 Diag(OpLoc, diag::ext_pseudo_dtor_on_void) << Base->getSourceRange();
6906 else {
6907 Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_pseudo_dtor_base_not_scalar)
6908 << ObjectType << Base->getSourceRange();
6909 return ExprError();
6910 }
6911 }
6912
6913 // C++ [expr.pseudo]p2:
6914 // [...] The cv-unqualified versions of the object type and of the type
6915 // designated by the pseudo-destructor-name shall be the same type.
6916 if (DestructedTypeInfo) {
6917 QualType DestructedType = DestructedTypeInfo->getType();
6918 SourceLocation DestructedTypeStart
6919 = DestructedTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getLocalSourceRange().getBegin();
6920 if (!DestructedType->isDependentType() && !ObjectType->isDependentType()) {
6921 if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestructedType, ObjectType)) {
6922 // Detect dot pseudo destructor calls on pointer objects, e.g.:
6923 // Foo *foo;
6924 // foo.~Foo();
6925 if (OpKind == tok::period && ObjectType->isPointerType() &&
6926 Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestructedType,
6927 ObjectType->getPointeeType())) {
6928 auto Diagnostic =
6929 Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_suggestion)
6930 << ObjectType << /*IsArrow=*/0 << Base->getSourceRange();
6931
6932 // Issue a fixit only when the destructor is valid.
6933 if (canRecoverDotPseudoDestructorCallsOnPointerObjects(
6934 *this, DestructedType))
6935 Diagnostic << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OpLoc, "->");
6936
6937 // Recover by setting the object type to the destructed type and the
6938 // operator to '->'.
6939 ObjectType = DestructedType;
6940 OpKind = tok::arrow;
6941 } else {
6942 Diag(DestructedTypeStart, diag::err_pseudo_dtor_type_mismatch)
6943 << ObjectType << DestructedType << Base->getSourceRange()
6944 << DestructedTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getLocalSourceRange();
6945
6946 // Recover by setting the destructed type to the object type.
6947 DestructedType = ObjectType;
6948 DestructedTypeInfo =
6949 Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(ObjectType, DestructedTypeStart);
6950 Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(DestructedTypeInfo);
6951 }
6952 } else if (DestructedType.getObjCLifetime() !=
6953 ObjectType.getObjCLifetime()) {
6954
6955 if (DestructedType.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None) {
6956 // Okay: just pretend that the user provided the correctly-qualified
6957 // type.
6958 } else {
6959 Diag(DestructedTypeStart, diag::err_arc_pseudo_dtor_inconstant_quals)
6960 << ObjectType << DestructedType << Base->getSourceRange()
6961 << DestructedTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getLocalSourceRange();
6962 }
6963
6964 // Recover by setting the destructed type to the object type.
6965 DestructedType = ObjectType;
6966 DestructedTypeInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(ObjectType,
6967 DestructedTypeStart);
6968 Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(DestructedTypeInfo);
6969 }
6970 }
6971 }
6972
6973 // C++ [expr.pseudo]p2:
6974 // [...] Furthermore, the two type-names in a pseudo-destructor-name of the
6975 // form
6976 //
6977 // ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] type-name :: ~ type-name
6978 //
6979 // shall designate the same scalar type.
6980 if (ScopeTypeInfo) {
6981 QualType ScopeType = ScopeTypeInfo->getType();
6982 if (!ScopeType->isDependentType() && !ObjectType->isDependentType() &&
6983 !Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ScopeType, ObjectType)) {
6984
6985 Diag(ScopeTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getLocalSourceRange().getBegin(),
6986 diag::err_pseudo_dtor_type_mismatch)
6987 << ObjectType << ScopeType << Base->getSourceRange()
6988 << ScopeTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getLocalSourceRange();
6989
6990 ScopeType = QualType();
6991 ScopeTypeInfo = nullptr;
6992 }
6993 }
6994
6995 Expr *Result
6996 = new (Context) CXXPseudoDestructorExpr(Context, Base,
6997 OpKind == tok::arrow, OpLoc,
6998 SS.getWithLocInContext(Context),
6999 ScopeTypeInfo,
7000 CCLoc,
7001 TildeLoc,
7002 Destructed);
7003
7004 return Result;
7005}
7006
7007ExprResult Sema::ActOnPseudoDestructorExpr(Scope *S, Expr *Base,
7008 SourceLocation OpLoc,
7009 tok::TokenKind OpKind,
7010 CXXScopeSpec &SS,
7011 UnqualifiedId &FirstTypeName,
7012 SourceLocation CCLoc,
7013 SourceLocation TildeLoc,
7014 UnqualifiedId &SecondTypeName) {
7015 assert((FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId ||
7016 FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) &&
7017 "Invalid first type name in pseudo-destructor");
7018 assert((SecondTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId ||
7019 SecondTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) &&
7020 "Invalid second type name in pseudo-destructor");
7021
7022 QualType ObjectType;
7023 if (CheckArrow(*this, ObjectType, Base, OpKind, OpLoc))
7024 return ExprError();
7025
7026 // Compute the object type that we should use for name lookup purposes. Only
7027 // record types and dependent types matter.
7028 ParsedType ObjectTypePtrForLookup;
7029 if (!SS.isSet()) {
7030 if (ObjectType->isRecordType())
7031 ObjectTypePtrForLookup = ParsedType::make(ObjectType);
7032 else if (ObjectType->isDependentType())
7033 ObjectTypePtrForLookup = ParsedType::make(Context.DependentTy);
7034 }
7035
7036 // Convert the name of the type being destructed (following the ~) into a
7037 // type (with source-location information).
7038 QualType DestructedType;
7039 TypeSourceInfo *DestructedTypeInfo = nullptr;
7040 PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destructed;
7041 if (SecondTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) {
7042 ParsedType T = getTypeName(*SecondTypeName.Identifier,
7043 SecondTypeName.StartLocation,
7044 S, &SS, true, false, ObjectTypePtrForLookup,
7045 /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
7046 if (!T &&
7047 ((SS.isSet() && !computeDeclContext(SS, false)) ||
7048 (!SS.isSet() && ObjectType->isDependentType()))) {
7049 // The name of the type being destroyed is a dependent name, and we
7050 // couldn't find anything useful in scope. Just store the identifier and
7051 // it's location, and we'll perform (qualified) name lookup again at
7052 // template instantiation time.
7053 Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(SecondTypeName.Identifier,
7054 SecondTypeName.StartLocation);
7055 } else if (!T) {
7056 Diag(SecondTypeName.StartLocation,
7057 diag::err_pseudo_dtor_destructor_non_type)
7058 << SecondTypeName.Identifier << ObjectType;
7059 if (isSFINAEContext())
7060 return ExprError();
7061
7062 // Recover by assuming we had the right type all along.
7063 DestructedType = ObjectType;
7064 } else
7065 DestructedType = GetTypeFromParser(T, &DestructedTypeInfo);
7066 } else {
7067 // Resolve the template-id to a type.
7068 TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = SecondTypeName.TemplateId;
7069 ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
7070 TemplateId->NumArgs);
7071 TypeResult T = ActOnTemplateIdType(S,
7072 TemplateId->SS,
7073 TemplateId->TemplateKWLoc,
7074 TemplateId->Template,
7075 TemplateId->Name,
7076 TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc,
7077 TemplateId->LAngleLoc,
7078 TemplateArgsPtr,
7079 TemplateId->RAngleLoc,
7080 /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
7081 if (T.isInvalid() || !T.get()) {
7082 // Recover by assuming we had the right type all along.
7083 DestructedType = ObjectType;
7084 } else
7085 DestructedType = GetTypeFromParser(T.get(), &DestructedTypeInfo);
7086 }
7087
7088 // If we've performed some kind of recovery, (re-)build the type source
7089 // information.
7090 if (!DestructedType.isNull()) {
7091 if (!DestructedTypeInfo)
7092 DestructedTypeInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(DestructedType,
7093 SecondTypeName.StartLocation);
7094 Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(DestructedTypeInfo);
7095 }
7096
7097 // Convert the name of the scope type (the type prior to '::') into a type.
7098 TypeSourceInfo *ScopeTypeInfo = nullptr;
7099 QualType ScopeType;
7100 if (FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId ||
7101 FirstTypeName.Identifier) {
7102 if (FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) {
7103 ParsedType T = getTypeName(*FirstTypeName.Identifier,
7104 FirstTypeName.StartLocation,
7105 S, &SS, true, false, ObjectTypePtrForLookup,
7106 /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
7107 if (!T) {
7108 Diag(FirstTypeName.StartLocation,
7109 diag::err_pseudo_dtor_destructor_non_type)
7110 << FirstTypeName.Identifier << ObjectType;
7111
7112 if (isSFINAEContext())
7113 return ExprError();
7114
7115 // Just drop this type. It's unnecessary anyway.
7116 ScopeType = QualType();
7117 } else
7118 ScopeType = GetTypeFromParser(T, &ScopeTypeInfo);
7119 } else {
7120 // Resolve the template-id to a type.
7121 TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = FirstTypeName.TemplateId;
7122 ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
7123 TemplateId->NumArgs);
7124 TypeResult T = ActOnTemplateIdType(S,
7125 TemplateId->SS,
7126 TemplateId->TemplateKWLoc,
7127 TemplateId->Template,
7128 TemplateId->Name,
7129 TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc,
7130 TemplateId->LAngleLoc,
7131 TemplateArgsPtr,
7132 TemplateId->RAngleLoc,
7133 /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
7134 if (T.isInvalid() || !T.get()) {
7135 // Recover by dropping this type.
7136 ScopeType = QualType();
7137 } else
7138 ScopeType = GetTypeFromParser(T.get(), &ScopeTypeInfo);
7139 }
7140 }
7141
7142 if (!ScopeType.isNull() && !ScopeTypeInfo)
7143 ScopeTypeInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(ScopeType,
7144 FirstTypeName.StartLocation);
7145
7146
7147 return BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(Base, OpLoc, OpKind, SS,
7148 ScopeTypeInfo, CCLoc, TildeLoc,
7149 Destructed);
7150}
7151
7152ExprResult Sema::ActOnPseudoDestructorExpr(Scope *S, Expr *Base,
7153 SourceLocation OpLoc,
7154 tok::TokenKind OpKind,
7155 SourceLocation TildeLoc,
7156 const DeclSpec& DS) {
7157 QualType ObjectType;
7158 if (CheckArrow(*this, ObjectType, Base, OpKind, OpLoc))
7159 return ExprError();
7160
7161 QualType T = BuildDecltypeType(DS.getRepAsExpr(), DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
7162 false);
7163
7164 TypeLocBuilder TLB;
7165 DecltypeTypeLoc DecltypeTL = TLB.push<DecltypeTypeLoc>(T);
7166 DecltypeTL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
7167 TypeSourceInfo *DestructedTypeInfo = TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(Context, T);
7168 PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destructed(DestructedTypeInfo);
7169
7170 return BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(Base, OpLoc, OpKind, CXXScopeSpec(),
7171 nullptr, SourceLocation(), TildeLoc,
7172 Destructed);
7173}
7174
7175ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXMemberCallExpr(Expr *E, NamedDecl *FoundDecl,
7176 CXXConversionDecl *Method,
7177 bool HadMultipleCandidates) {
7178 // Convert the expression to match the conversion function's implicit object
7179 // parameter.
7180 ExprResult Exp = PerformObjectArgumentInitialization(E, /*Qualifier=*/nullptr,
7181 FoundDecl, Method);
7182 if (Exp.isInvalid())
7183 return true;
7184
7185 if (Method->getParent()->isLambda() &&
7186 Method->getConversionType()->isBlockPointerType()) {
7187 // This is a lambda coversion to block pointer; check if the argument
7188 // was a LambdaExpr.
7189 Expr *SubE = E;
7190 CastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(SubE);
7191 if (CE && CE->getCastKind() == CK_NoOp)
7192 SubE = CE->getSubExpr();
7193 SubE = SubE->IgnoreParens();
7194 if (CXXBindTemporaryExpr *BE = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(SubE))
7195 SubE = BE->getSubExpr();
7196 if (isa<LambdaExpr>(SubE)) {
7197 // For the conversion to block pointer on a lambda expression, we
7198 // construct a special BlockLiteral instead; this doesn't really make
7199 // a difference in ARC, but outside of ARC the resulting block literal
7200 // follows the normal lifetime rules for block literals instead of being
7201 // autoreleased.
7202 DiagnosticErrorTrap Trap(Diags);
7203 PushExpressionEvaluationContext(
7204 ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
7205 ExprResult BlockExp = BuildBlockForLambdaConversion(
7206 Exp.get()->getExprLoc(), Exp.get()->getExprLoc(), Method, Exp.get());
7207 PopExpressionEvaluationContext();
7208
7209 if (BlockExp.isInvalid())
7210 Diag(Exp.get()->getExprLoc(), diag::note_lambda_to_block_conv);
7211 return BlockExp;
7212 }
7213 }
7214
7215 MemberExpr *ME =
7216 BuildMemberExpr(Exp.get(), /*IsArrow=*/false, SourceLocation(),
7217 NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), SourceLocation(), Method,
7218 DeclAccessPair::make(FoundDecl, FoundDecl->getAccess()),
7219 HadMultipleCandidates, DeclarationNameInfo(),
7220 Context.BoundMemberTy, VK_RValue, OK_Ordinary);
7221
7222 QualType ResultType = Method->getReturnType();
7223 ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultType);
7224 ResultType = ResultType.getNonLValueExprType(Context);
7225
7226 CXXMemberCallExpr *CE = CXXMemberCallExpr::Create(
7227 Context, ME, /*Args=*/{}, ResultType, VK, Exp.get()->getEndLoc());
7228
7229 if (CheckFunctionCall(Method, CE,
7230 Method->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()))
7231 return ExprError();
7232
7233 return CE;
7234}
7235
7236ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXNoexceptExpr(SourceLocation KeyLoc, Expr *Operand,
7237 SourceLocation RParen) {
7238 // If the operand is an unresolved lookup expression, the expression is ill-
7239 // formed per [over.over]p1, because overloaded function names cannot be used
7240 // without arguments except in explicit contexts.
7241 ExprResult R = CheckPlaceholderExpr(Operand);
7242 if (R.isInvalid())
7243 return R;
7244
7245 // The operand may have been modified when checking the placeholder type.
7246 Operand = R.get();
7247
7248 if (!inTemplateInstantiation() && Operand->HasSideEffects(Context, false)) {
7249 // The expression operand for noexcept is in an unevaluated expression
7250 // context, so side effects could result in unintended consequences.
7251 Diag(Operand->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_side_effects_unevaluated_context);
7252 }
7253
7254 CanThrowResult CanThrow = canThrow(Operand);
7255 return new (Context)
7256 CXXNoexceptExpr(Context.BoolTy, Operand, CanThrow, KeyLoc, RParen);
7257}
7258
7259ExprResult Sema::ActOnNoexceptExpr(SourceLocation KeyLoc, SourceLocation,
7260 Expr *Operand, SourceLocation RParen) {
7261 return BuildCXXNoexceptExpr(KeyLoc, Operand, RParen);
7262}
7263
7264static bool IsSpecialDiscardedValue(Expr *E) {
7265 // In C++11, discarded-value expressions of a certain form are special,
7266 // according to [expr]p10:
7267 // The lvalue-to-rvalue conversion (4.1) is applied only if the
7268 // expression is an lvalue of volatile-qualified type and it has
7269 // one of the following forms:
7270 E = E->IgnoreParens();
7271
7272 // - id-expression (5.1.1),
7273 if (isa<DeclRefExpr>(E))
7274 return true;
7275
7276 // - subscripting (5.2.1),
7277 if (isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E))
7278 return true;
7279
7280 // - class member access (5.2.5),
7281 if (isa<MemberExpr>(E))
7282 return true;
7283
7284 // - indirection (5.3.1),
7285 if (UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E))
7286 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_Deref)
7287 return true;
7288
7289 if (BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
7290 // - pointer-to-member operation (5.5),
7291 if (BO->isPtrMemOp())
7292 return true;
7293
7294 // - comma expression (5.18) where the right operand is one of the above.
7295 if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_Comma)
7296 return IsSpecialDiscardedValue(BO->getRHS());
7297 }
7298
7299 // - conditional expression (5.16) where both the second and the third
7300 // operands are one of the above, or
7301 if (ConditionalOperator *CO = dyn_cast<ConditionalOperator>(E))
7302 return IsSpecialDiscardedValue(CO->getTrueExpr()) &&
7303 IsSpecialDiscardedValue(CO->getFalseExpr());
7304 // The related edge case of "*x ?: *x".
7305 if (BinaryConditionalOperator *BCO =
7306 dyn_cast<BinaryConditionalOperator>(E)) {
7307 if (OpaqueValueExpr *OVE = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(BCO->getTrueExpr()))
7308 return IsSpecialDiscardedValue(OVE->getSourceExpr()) &&
7309 IsSpecialDiscardedValue(BCO->getFalseExpr());
7310 }
7311
7312 // Objective-C++ extensions to the rule.
7313 if (isa<PseudoObjectExpr>(E) || isa<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E))
7314 return true;
7315
7316 return false;
7317}
7318
7319/// Perform the conversions required for an expression used in a
7320/// context that ignores the result.
7321ExprResult Sema::IgnoredValueConversions(Expr *E) {
7322 if (E->hasPlaceholderType()) {
7323 ExprResult result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(E);
7324 if (result.isInvalid()) return E;
7325 E = result.get();
7326 }
7327
7328 // C99 6.3.2.1:
7329 // [Except in specific positions,] an lvalue that does not have
7330 // array type is converted to the value stored in the
7331 // designated object (and is no longer an lvalue).
7332 if (E->isRValue()) {
7333 // In C, function designators (i.e. expressions of function type)
7334 // are r-values, but we still want to do function-to-pointer decay
7335 // on them. This is both technically correct and convenient for
7336 // some clients.
7337 if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && E->getType()->isFunctionType())
7338 return DefaultFunctionArrayConversion(E);
7339
7340 return E;
7341 }
7342
7343 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
7344 // The C++11 standard defines the notion of a discarded-value expression;
7345 // normally, we don't need to do anything to handle it, but if it is a
7346 // volatile lvalue with a special form, we perform an lvalue-to-rvalue
7347 // conversion.
7348 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && E->isGLValue() &&
7349 E->getType().isVolatileQualified() &&
7350 IsSpecialDiscardedValue(E)) {
7351 ExprResult Res = DefaultLvalueConversion(E);
7352 if (Res.isInvalid())
7353 return E;
7354 E = Res.get();
7355 }
7356
7357 // C++1z:
7358 // If the expression is a prvalue after this optional conversion, the
7359 // temporary materialization conversion is applied.
7360 //
7361 // We skip this step: IR generation is able to synthesize the storage for
7362 // itself in the aggregate case, and adding the extra node to the AST is
7363 // just clutter.
7364 // FIXME: We don't emit lifetime markers for the temporaries due to this.
7365 // FIXME: Do any other AST consumers care about this?
7366 return E;
7367 }
7368
7369 // GCC seems to also exclude expressions of incomplete enum type.
7370 if (const EnumType *T = E->getType()->getAs<EnumType>()) {
7371 if (!T->getDecl()->isComplete()) {
7372 // FIXME: stupid workaround for a codegen bug!
7373 E = ImpCastExprToType(E, Context.VoidTy, CK_ToVoid).get();
7374 return E;
7375 }
7376 }
7377
7378 ExprResult Res = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(E);
7379 if (Res.isInvalid())
7380 return E;
7381 E = Res.get();
7382
7383 if (!E->getType()->isVoidType())
7384 RequireCompleteType(E->getExprLoc(), E->getType(),
7385 diag::err_incomplete_type);
7386 return E;
7387}
7388
7389// If we can unambiguously determine whether Var can never be used
7390// in a constant expression, return true.
7391// - if the variable and its initializer are non-dependent, then
7392// we can unambiguously check if the variable is a constant expression.
7393// - if the initializer is not value dependent - we can determine whether
7394// it can be used to initialize a constant expression. If Init can not
7395// be used to initialize a constant expression we conclude that Var can
7396// never be a constant expression.
7397// - FXIME: if the initializer is dependent, we can still do some analysis and
7398// identify certain cases unambiguously as non-const by using a Visitor:
7399// - such as those that involve odr-use of a ParmVarDecl, involve a new
7400// delete, lambda-expr, dynamic-cast, reinterpret-cast etc...
7401static inline bool VariableCanNeverBeAConstantExpression(VarDecl *Var,
7402 ASTContext &Context) {
7403 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(Var)) return true;
7404 const VarDecl *DefVD = nullptr;
7405
7406 // If there is no initializer - this can not be a constant expression.
7407 if (!Var->getAnyInitializer(DefVD)) return true;
7408 assert(DefVD);
7409 if (DefVD->isWeak()) return false;
7410 EvaluatedStmt *Eval = DefVD->ensureEvaluatedStmt();
7411
7412 Expr *Init = cast<Expr>(Eval->Value);
7413
7414 if (Var->getType()->isDependentType() || Init->isValueDependent()) {
7415 // FIXME: Teach the constant evaluator to deal with the non-dependent parts
7416 // of value-dependent expressions, and use it here to determine whether the
7417 // initializer is a potential constant expression.
7418 return false;
7419 }
7420
7421 return !Var->isUsableInConstantExpressions(Context);
7422}
7423
7424/// Check if the current lambda has any potential captures
7425/// that must be captured by any of its enclosing lambdas that are ready to
7426/// capture. If there is a lambda that can capture a nested
7427/// potential-capture, go ahead and do so. Also, check to see if any
7428/// variables are uncaptureable or do not involve an odr-use so do not
7429/// need to be captured.
7430
7431static void CheckIfAnyEnclosingLambdasMustCaptureAnyPotentialCaptures(
7432 Expr *const FE, LambdaScopeInfo *const CurrentLSI, Sema &S) {
7433
7434 assert(!S.isUnevaluatedContext());
7435 assert(S.CurContext->isDependentContext());
7436#ifndef NDEBUG
7437 DeclContext *DC = S.CurContext;
7438 while (DC && isa<CapturedDecl>(DC))
7439 DC = DC->getParent();
7440 assert(
7441 CurrentLSI->CallOperator == DC &&
7442 "The current call operator must be synchronized with Sema's CurContext");
7443#endif // NDEBUG
7444
7445 const bool IsFullExprInstantiationDependent = FE->isInstantiationDependent();
7446
7447 // All the potentially captureable variables in the current nested
7448 // lambda (within a generic outer lambda), must be captured by an
7449 // outer lambda that is enclosed within a non-dependent context.
7450 CurrentLSI->visitPotentialCaptures([&] (VarDecl *Var, Expr *VarExpr) {
7451 // If the variable is clearly identified as non-odr-used and the full
7452 // expression is not instantiation dependent, only then do we not
7453 // need to check enclosing lambda's for speculative captures.
7454 // For e.g.:
7455 // Even though 'x' is not odr-used, it should be captured.
7456 // int test() {
7457 // const int x = 10;
7458 // auto L = [=](auto a) {
7459 // (void) +x + a;
7460 // };
7461 // }
7462 if (CurrentLSI->isVariableExprMarkedAsNonODRUsed(VarExpr) &&
7463 !IsFullExprInstantiationDependent)
7464 return;
7465
7466 // If we have a capture-capable lambda for the variable, go ahead and
7467 // capture the variable in that lambda (and all its enclosing lambdas).
7468 if (const Optional<unsigned> Index =
7469 getStackIndexOfNearestEnclosingCaptureCapableLambda(
7470 S.FunctionScopes, Var, S))
7471 S.MarkCaptureUsedInEnclosingContext(Var, VarExpr->getExprLoc(),
7472 Index.getValue());
7473 const bool IsVarNeverAConstantExpression =
7474 VariableCanNeverBeAConstantExpression(Var, S.Context);
7475 if (!IsFullExprInstantiationDependent || IsVarNeverAConstantExpression) {
7476 // This full expression is not instantiation dependent or the variable
7477 // can not be used in a constant expression - which means
7478 // this variable must be odr-used here, so diagnose a
7479 // capture violation early, if the variable is un-captureable.
7480 // This is purely for diagnosing errors early. Otherwise, this
7481 // error would get diagnosed when the lambda becomes capture ready.
7482 QualType CaptureType, DeclRefType;
7483 SourceLocation ExprLoc = VarExpr->getExprLoc();
7484 if (S.tryCaptureVariable(Var, ExprLoc, S.TryCapture_Implicit,
7485 /*EllipsisLoc*/ SourceLocation(),
7486 /*BuildAndDiagnose*/false, CaptureType,
7487 DeclRefType, nullptr)) {
7488 // We will never be able to capture this variable, and we need
7489 // to be able to in any and all instantiations, so diagnose it.
7490 S.tryCaptureVariable(Var, ExprLoc, S.TryCapture_Implicit,
7491 /*EllipsisLoc*/ SourceLocation(),
7492 /*BuildAndDiagnose*/true, CaptureType,
7493 DeclRefType, nullptr);
7494 }
7495 }
7496 });
7497
7498 // Check if 'this' needs to be captured.
7499 if (CurrentLSI->hasPotentialThisCapture()) {
7500 // If we have a capture-capable lambda for 'this', go ahead and capture
7501 // 'this' in that lambda (and all its enclosing lambdas).
7502 if (const Optional<unsigned> Index =
7503 getStackIndexOfNearestEnclosingCaptureCapableLambda(
7504 S.FunctionScopes, /*0 is 'this'*/ nullptr, S)) {
7505 const unsigned FunctionScopeIndexOfCapturableLambda = Index.getValue();
7506 S.CheckCXXThisCapture(CurrentLSI->PotentialThisCaptureLocation,
7507 /*Explicit*/ false, /*BuildAndDiagnose*/ true,
7508 &FunctionScopeIndexOfCapturableLambda);
7509 }
7510 }
7511
7512 // Reset all the potential captures at the end of each full-expression.
7513 CurrentLSI->clearPotentialCaptures();
7514}
7515
7516static ExprResult attemptRecovery(Sema &SemaRef,
7517 const TypoCorrectionConsumer &Consumer,
7518 const TypoCorrection &TC) {
7519 LookupResult R(SemaRef, Consumer.getLookupResult().getLookupNameInfo(),
7520 Consumer.getLookupResult().getLookupKind());
7521 const CXXScopeSpec *SS = Consumer.getSS();
7522 CXXScopeSpec NewSS;
7523
7524 // Use an approprate CXXScopeSpec for building the expr.
7525 if (auto *NNS = TC.getCorrectionSpecifier())
7526 NewSS.MakeTrivial(SemaRef.Context, NNS, TC.getCorrectionRange());
7527 else if (SS && !TC.WillReplaceSpecifier())
7528 NewSS = *SS;
7529
7530 if (auto *ND = TC.getFoundDecl()) {
7531 R.setLookupName(ND->getDeclName());
7532 R.addDecl(ND);
7533 if (ND->isCXXClassMember()) {
7534 // Figure out the correct naming class to add to the LookupResult.
7535 CXXRecordDecl *Record = nullptr;
7536 if (auto *NNS = TC.getCorrectionSpecifier())
7537 Record = NNS->getAsType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
7538 if (!Record)
7539 Record =
7540 dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ND->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext());
7541 if (Record)
7542 R.setNamingClass(Record);
7543
7544 // Detect and handle the case where the decl might be an implicit
7545 // member.
7546 bool MightBeImplicitMember;
7547 if (!Consumer.isAddressOfOperand())
7548 MightBeImplicitMember = true;
7549 else if (!NewSS.isEmpty())
7550 MightBeImplicitMember = false;
7551 else if (R.isOverloadedResult())
7552 MightBeImplicitMember = false;
7553 else if (R.isUnresolvableResult())
7554 MightBeImplicitMember = true;
7555 else
7556 MightBeImplicitMember = isa<FieldDecl>(ND) ||
7557 isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(ND) ||
7558 isa<MSPropertyDecl>(ND);
7559
7560 if (MightBeImplicitMember)
7561 return SemaRef.BuildPossibleImplicitMemberExpr(
7562 NewSS, /*TemplateKWLoc*/ SourceLocation(), R,
7563 /*TemplateArgs*/ nullptr, /*S*/ nullptr);
7564 } else if (auto *Ivar = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarDecl>(ND)) {
7565 return SemaRef.LookupInObjCMethod(R, Consumer.getScope(),
7566 Ivar->getIdentifier());
7567 }
7568 }
7569
7570 return SemaRef.BuildDeclarationNameExpr(NewSS, R, /*NeedsADL*/ false,
7571 /*AcceptInvalidDecl*/ true);
7572}
7573
7574namespace {
7575class FindTypoExprs : public RecursiveASTVisitor<FindTypoExprs> {
7576 llvm::SmallSetVector<TypoExpr *, 2> &TypoExprs;
7577
7578public:
7579 explicit FindTypoExprs(llvm::SmallSetVector<TypoExpr *, 2> &TypoExprs)
7580 : TypoExprs(TypoExprs) {}
7581 bool VisitTypoExpr(TypoExpr *TE) {
7582 TypoExprs.insert(TE);
7583 return true;
7584 }
7585};
7586
7587class TransformTypos : public TreeTransform<TransformTypos> {
7588 typedef TreeTransform<TransformTypos> BaseTransform;
7589
7590 VarDecl *InitDecl; // A decl to avoid as a correction because it is in the
7591 // process of being initialized.
7592 llvm::function_ref<ExprResult(Expr *)> ExprFilter;
7593 llvm::SmallSetVector<TypoExpr *, 2> TypoExprs, AmbiguousTypoExprs;
7594 llvm::SmallDenseMap<TypoExpr *, ExprResult, 2> TransformCache;
7595 llvm::SmallDenseMap<OverloadExpr *, Expr *, 4> OverloadResolution;
7596
7597 /// Emit diagnostics for all of the TypoExprs encountered.
7598 /// If the TypoExprs were successfully corrected, then the diagnostics should
7599 /// suggest the corrections. Otherwise the diagnostics will not suggest
7600 /// anything (having been passed an empty TypoCorrection).
7601 void EmitAllDiagnostics() {
7602 for (TypoExpr *TE : TypoExprs) {
7603 auto &State = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE);
7604 if (State.DiagHandler) {
7605 TypoCorrection TC = State.Consumer->getCurrentCorrection();
7606 ExprResult Replacement = TransformCache[TE];
7607
7608 // Extract the NamedDecl from the transformed TypoExpr and add it to the
7609 // TypoCorrection, replacing the existing decls. This ensures the right
7610 // NamedDecl is used in diagnostics e.g. in the case where overload
7611 // resolution was used to select one from several possible decls that
7612 // had been stored in the TypoCorrection.
7613 if (auto *ND = getDeclFromExpr(
7614 Replacement.isInvalid() ? nullptr : Replacement.get()))
7615 TC.setCorrectionDecl(ND);
7616
7617 State.DiagHandler(TC);
7618 }
7619 SemaRef.clearDelayedTypo(TE);
7620 }
7621 }
7622
7623 /// If corrections for the first TypoExpr have been exhausted for a
7624 /// given combination of the other TypoExprs, retry those corrections against
7625 /// the next combination of substitutions for the other TypoExprs by advancing
7626 /// to the next potential correction of the second TypoExpr. For the second
7627 /// and subsequent TypoExprs, if its stream of corrections has been exhausted,
7628 /// the stream is reset and the next TypoExpr's stream is advanced by one (a
7629 /// TypoExpr's correction stream is advanced by removing the TypoExpr from the
7630 /// TransformCache). Returns true if there is still any untried combinations
7631 /// of corrections.
7632 bool CheckAndAdvanceTypoExprCorrectionStreams() {
7633 for (auto TE : TypoExprs) {
7634 auto &State = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE);
7635 TransformCache.erase(TE);
7636 if (!State.Consumer->finished())
7637 return true;
7638 State.Consumer->resetCorrectionStream();
7639 }
7640 return false;
7641 }
7642
7643 NamedDecl *getDeclFromExpr(Expr *E) {
7644 if (auto *OE = dyn_cast_or_null<OverloadExpr>(E))
7645 E = OverloadResolution[OE];
7646
7647 if (!E)
7648 return nullptr;
7649 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
7650 return DRE->getFoundDecl();
7651 if (auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
7652 return ME->getFoundDecl();
7653 // FIXME: Add any other expr types that could be be seen by the delayed typo
7654 // correction TreeTransform for which the corresponding TypoCorrection could
7655 // contain multiple decls.
7656 return nullptr;
7657 }
7658
7659 ExprResult TryTransform(Expr *E) {
7660 Sema::SFINAETrap Trap(SemaRef);
7661 ExprResult Res = TransformExpr(E);
7662 if (Trap.hasErrorOccurred() || Res.isInvalid())
7663 return ExprError();
7664
7665 return ExprFilter(Res.get());
7666 }
7667
7668public:
7669 TransformTypos(Sema &SemaRef, VarDecl *InitDecl, llvm::function_ref<ExprResult(Expr *)> Filter)
7670 : BaseTransform(SemaRef), InitDecl(InitDecl), ExprFilter(Filter) {}
7671
7672 ExprResult RebuildCallExpr(Expr *Callee, SourceLocation LParenLoc,
7673 MultiExprArg Args,
7674 SourceLocation RParenLoc,
7675 Expr *ExecConfig = nullptr) {
7676 auto Result = BaseTransform::RebuildCallExpr(Callee, LParenLoc, Args,
7677 RParenLoc, ExecConfig);
7678 if (auto *OE = dyn_cast<OverloadExpr>(Callee)) {
7679 if (Result.isUsable()) {
7680 Expr *ResultCall = Result.get();
7681 if (auto *BE = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(ResultCall))
7682 ResultCall = BE->getSubExpr();
7683 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(ResultCall))
7684 OverloadResolution[OE] = CE->getCallee();
7685 }
7686 }
7687 return Result;
7688 }
7689
7690 ExprResult TransformLambdaExpr(LambdaExpr *E) { return Owned(E); }
7691
7692 ExprResult TransformBlockExpr(BlockExpr *E) { return Owned(E); }
7693
7694 ExprResult Transform(Expr *E) {
7695 ExprResult Res;
7696 while (true) {
7697 Res = TryTransform(E);
7698
7699 // Exit if either the transform was valid or if there were no TypoExprs
7700 // to transform that still have any untried correction candidates..
7701 if (!Res.isInvalid() ||
7702 !CheckAndAdvanceTypoExprCorrectionStreams())
7703 break;
7704 }
7705
7706 // Ensure none of the TypoExprs have multiple typo correction candidates
7707 // with the same edit length that pass all the checks and filters.
7708 // TODO: Properly handle various permutations of possible corrections when
7709 // there is more than one potentially ambiguous typo correction.
7710 // Also, disable typo correction while attempting the transform when
7711 // handling potentially ambiguous typo corrections as any new TypoExprs will
7712 // have been introduced by the application of one of the correction
7713 // candidates and add little to no value if corrected.
7714 SemaRef.DisableTypoCorrection = true;
7715 while (!AmbiguousTypoExprs.empty()) {
7716 auto TE = AmbiguousTypoExprs.back();
7717 auto Cached = TransformCache[TE];
7718 auto &State = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE);
7719 State.Consumer->saveCurrentPosition();
7720 TransformCache.erase(TE);
7721 if (!TryTransform(E).isInvalid()) {
7722 State.Consumer->resetCorrectionStream();
7723 TransformCache.erase(TE);
7724 Res = ExprError();
7725 break;
7726 }
7727 AmbiguousTypoExprs.remove(TE);
7728 State.Consumer->restoreSavedPosition();
7729 TransformCache[TE] = Cached;
7730 }
7731 SemaRef.DisableTypoCorrection = false;
7732
7733 // Ensure that all of the TypoExprs within the current Expr have been found.
7734 if (!Res.isUsable())
7735 FindTypoExprs(TypoExprs).TraverseStmt(E);
7736
7737 EmitAllDiagnostics();
7738
7739 return Res;
7740 }
7741
7742 ExprResult TransformTypoExpr(TypoExpr *E) {
7743 // If the TypoExpr hasn't been seen before, record it. Otherwise, return the
7744 // cached transformation result if there is one and the TypoExpr isn't the
7745 // first one that was encountered.
7746 auto &CacheEntry = TransformCache[E];
7747 if (!TypoExprs.insert(E) && !CacheEntry.isUnset()) {
7748 return CacheEntry;
7749 }
7750
7751 auto &State = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(E);
7752 assert(State.Consumer && "Cannot transform a cleared TypoExpr");
7753
7754 // For the first TypoExpr and an uncached TypoExpr, find the next likely
7755 // typo correction and return it.
7756 while (TypoCorrection TC = State.Consumer->getNextCorrection()) {
7757 if (InitDecl && TC.getFoundDecl() == InitDecl)
7758 continue;
7759 // FIXME: If we would typo-correct to an invalid declaration, it's
7760 // probably best to just suppress all errors from this typo correction.
7761 ExprResult NE = State.RecoveryHandler ?
7762 State.RecoveryHandler(SemaRef, E, TC) :
7763 attemptRecovery(SemaRef, *State.Consumer, TC);
7764 if (!NE.isInvalid()) {
7765 // Check whether there may be a second viable correction with the same
7766 // edit distance; if so, remember this TypoExpr may have an ambiguous
7767 // correction so it can be more thoroughly vetted later.
7768 TypoCorrection Next;
7769 if ((Next = State.Consumer->peekNextCorrection()) &&
7770 Next.getEditDistance(false) == TC.getEditDistance(false)) {
7771 AmbiguousTypoExprs.insert(E);
7772 } else {
7773 AmbiguousTypoExprs.remove(E);
7774 }
7775 assert(!NE.isUnset() &&
7776 "Typo was transformed into a valid-but-null ExprResult");
7777 return CacheEntry = NE;
7778 }
7779 }
7780 return CacheEntry = ExprError();
7781 }
7782};
7783}
7784
7785ExprResult
7786Sema::CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(Expr *E, VarDecl *InitDecl,
7787 llvm::function_ref<ExprResult(Expr *)> Filter) {
7788 // If the current evaluation context indicates there are uncorrected typos
7789 // and the current expression isn't guaranteed to not have typos, try to
7790 // resolve any TypoExpr nodes that might be in the expression.
7791 if (E && !ExprEvalContexts.empty() && ExprEvalContexts.back().NumTypos &&
7792 (E->isTypeDependent() || E->isValueDependent() ||
7793 E->isInstantiationDependent())) {
7794 auto TyposResolved = DelayedTypos.size();
7795 auto Result = TransformTypos(*this, InitDecl, Filter).Transform(E);
7796 TyposResolved -= DelayedTypos.size();
7797 if (Result.isInvalid() || Result.get() != E) {
7798 ExprEvalContexts.back().NumTypos -= TyposResolved;
7799 return Result;
7800 }
7801 assert(TyposResolved == 0 && "Corrected typo but got same Expr back?");
7802 }
7803 return E;
7804}
7805
7806ExprResult Sema::ActOnFinishFullExpr(Expr *FE, SourceLocation CC,
7807 bool DiscardedValue,
7808 bool IsConstexpr) {
7809 ExprResult FullExpr = FE;
7810
7811 if (!FullExpr.get())
7812 return ExprError();
7813
7814 if (DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(FullExpr.get()))
7815 return ExprError();
7816
7817 if (DiscardedValue) {
7818 // Top-level expressions default to 'id' when we're in a debugger.
7819 if (getLangOpts().DebuggerCastResultToId &&
7820 FullExpr.get()->getType() == Context.UnknownAnyTy) {
7821 FullExpr = forceUnknownAnyToType(FullExpr.get(), Context.getObjCIdType());
7822 if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
7823 return ExprError();
7824 }
7825
7826 FullExpr = CheckPlaceholderExpr(FullExpr.get());
7827 if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
7828 return ExprError();
7829
7830 FullExpr = IgnoredValueConversions(FullExpr.get());
7831 if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
7832 return ExprError();
7833
7834 DiagnoseUnusedExprResult(FullExpr.get());
7835 }
7836
7837 FullExpr = CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(FullExpr.get());
7838 if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
7839 return ExprError();
7840
7841 CheckCompletedExpr(FullExpr.get(), CC, IsConstexpr);
7842
7843 // At the end of this full expression (which could be a deeply nested
7844 // lambda), if there is a potential capture within the nested lambda,
7845 // have the outer capture-able lambda try and capture it.
7846 // Consider the following code:
7847 // void f(int, int);
7848 // void f(const int&, double);
7849 // void foo() {
7850 // const int x = 10, y = 20;
7851 // auto L = [=](auto a) {
7852 // auto M = [=](auto b) {
7853 // f(x, b); <-- requires x to be captured by L and M
7854 // f(y, a); <-- requires y to be captured by L, but not all Ms
7855 // };
7856 // };
7857 // }
7858
7859 // FIXME: Also consider what happens for something like this that involves
7860 // the gnu-extension statement-expressions or even lambda-init-captures:
7861 // void f() {
7862 // const int n = 0;
7863 // auto L = [&](auto a) {
7864 // +n + ({ 0; a; });
7865 // };
7866 // }
7867 //
7868 // Here, we see +n, and then the full-expression 0; ends, so we don't
7869 // capture n (and instead remove it from our list of potential captures),
7870 // and then the full-expression +n + ({ 0; }); ends, but it's too late
7871 // for us to see that we need to capture n after all.
7872
7873 LambdaScopeInfo *const CurrentLSI =
7874 getCurLambda(/*IgnoreCapturedRegions=*/true);
7875 // FIXME: PR 17877 showed that getCurLambda() can return a valid pointer
7876 // even if CurContext is not a lambda call operator. Refer to that Bug Report
7877 // for an example of the code that might cause this asynchrony.
7878 // By ensuring we are in the context of a lambda's call operator
7879 // we can fix the bug (we only need to check whether we need to capture
7880 // if we are within a lambda's body); but per the comments in that
7881 // PR, a proper fix would entail :
7882 // "Alternative suggestion:
7883 // - Add to Sema an integer holding the smallest (outermost) scope
7884 // index that we are *lexically* within, and save/restore/set to
7885 // FunctionScopes.size() in InstantiatingTemplate's
7886 // constructor/destructor.
7887 // - Teach the handful of places that iterate over FunctionScopes to
7888 // stop at the outermost enclosing lexical scope."
7889 DeclContext *DC = CurContext;
7890 while (DC && isa<CapturedDecl>(DC))
7891 DC = DC->getParent();
7892 const bool IsInLambdaDeclContext = isLambdaCallOperator(DC);
7893 if (IsInLambdaDeclContext && CurrentLSI &&
7894 CurrentLSI->hasPotentialCaptures() && !FullExpr.isInvalid())
7895 CheckIfAnyEnclosingLambdasMustCaptureAnyPotentialCaptures(FE, CurrentLSI,
7896 *this);
7897 return MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(FullExpr);
7898}
7899
7900StmtResult Sema::ActOnFinishFullStmt(Stmt *FullStmt) {
7901 if (!FullStmt) return StmtError();
7902
7903 return MaybeCreateStmtWithCleanups(FullStmt);
7904}
7905
7906Sema::IfExistsResult
7907Sema::CheckMicrosoftIfExistsSymbol(Scope *S,
7908 CXXScopeSpec &SS,
7909 const DeclarationNameInfo &TargetNameInfo) {
7910 DeclarationName TargetName = TargetNameInfo.getName();
7911 if (!TargetName)
7912 return IER_DoesNotExist;
7913
7914 // If the name itself is dependent, then the result is dependent.
7915 if (TargetName.isDependentName())
7916 return IER_Dependent;
7917
7918 // Do the redeclaration lookup in the current scope.
7919 LookupResult R(*this, TargetNameInfo, Sema::LookupAnyName,
7920 Sema::NotForRedeclaration);
7921 LookupParsedName(R, S, &SS);
7922 R.suppressDiagnostics();
7923
7924 switch (R.getResultKind()) {
7925 case LookupResult::Found:
7926 case LookupResult::FoundOverloaded:
7927 case LookupResult::FoundUnresolvedValue:
7928 case LookupResult::Ambiguous:
7929 return IER_Exists;
7930
7931 case LookupResult::NotFound:
7932 return IER_DoesNotExist;
7933
7934 case LookupResult::NotFoundInCurrentInstantiation:
7935 return IER_Dependent;
7936 }
7937
7938 llvm_unreachable("Invalid LookupResult Kind!");
7939}
7940
7941Sema::IfExistsResult
7942Sema::CheckMicrosoftIfExistsSymbol(Scope *S, SourceLocation KeywordLoc,
7943 bool IsIfExists, CXXScopeSpec &SS,
7944 UnqualifiedId &Name) {
7945 DeclarationNameInfo TargetNameInfo = GetNameFromUnqualifiedId(Name);
7946
7947 // Check for an unexpanded parameter pack.
7948 auto UPPC = IsIfExists ? UPPC_IfExists : UPPC_IfNotExists;
7949 if (DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(SS, UPPC) ||
7950 DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(TargetNameInfo, UPPC))
7951 return IER_Error;
7952
7953 return CheckMicrosoftIfExistsSymbol(S, SS, TargetNameInfo);
7954}
